{"text": "I started playing Space Tyrant as a beta-tester and instantly was amazed by its style and concept. You are taking the role of a tyrant in space who wants to conquer the universe. You start your first cycle with one race, the \"Hoplite\", gathering artifacts, perks, permanent tactics and permanent cards, to boost up your experience. It is impossible to get all race-based unlocks through one cycle, but through the random-generated maps replaying does not get boring in the least. Although I have almost 110h of gameplay I still did not unlock everything there is to unlock! And on top of that I never getting bored by the game's dark humor. The only bad thing (which is not really bad) about this game is, that the spacebattles are mostly fought automatically. You can \"only\" activate  skills and choose tactics at the beginning of each battle. Pros: - replayability - dark humor - random maps - unlockables Cons: - more or less automatically fought battles  To sum it up, I can recommend it in every way. In my opinion is worth the 20€.", "appid": "562230", "steamid": "profiles/76561198057846171", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1547812800.0}
