{"text": "As big as a fan i am of 2D/2.5D games, i must say this is one of the best. Child of Light controls are like most of the 2D games but what makes this special is the combat system! The combat of this game is turn based strategic combat. Not completely tho! It has its unique way of dividing its combat system from other games like this. The plot and story is fantastic! And as a game from ubisoft its graphics is beautiful for a 2D games and the enviroment. One of the best looking artistic game i've played. And the OST/Soundtracks of this game are complete masterpiece! Another thing that i loved was how a game like this can have such meaningful side quests and interesting world. Overall its a masterpiece of its genre! My rating is - 9.5/10 I recommend this game if you're looking for one of the best rides in your life!", "appid": "256290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198185407950", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1500120000.0}
{"text": "This is a fun, hectic space top down shooter. You take control of a spaceship and fight against gradually more difficult waves of aliens.   Your ship can be equipped with various weapons, ranging from missiles over sonic bursts to lasers. Each wave generates more and occasionally new enemies, each with unique and interesting attack patterns. At the end of each wave, you can spend the collected money on new or upgraded weapons and improvements for your ship.   Besides the fiddly menu design, the visuals look great and together with the catchy music it gives the game a unique vibe. The gameplay feels fast and snappy, but it can get a bit convoluted when many enemies are on screen. The game offers many steam achievements, which get unlocked by simply playing. The game can be completed in roughly 3 to 7 hours, depending on if you hunt for the achievements.  This is an entertaining game, which can get quite addicting too.  Regarding the low price, it is definitely worth a pick if you like games like this.", "appid": "679120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198112599967", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588593600.0}
{"text": "I got the game to literally swan-dive from the roof of the mansion and lock Winston in the freezer. Pros:   1. Swan-diving head first into the floor from a great height is hilarious. Best ragdoll 10/10 2. The bone break sound effect sounds like someone chomping on a raw cabbage.  3. Winston's rightful place is in the freezer. I'm glad we have the option to abandon him there. Cons: 1. You don't own the game and you're not performing these fantastic feats yourself. 2. For every person who doesn't buy the game there is +1 Winston roaming freely, away from his natural habitat - the freezer.", "appid": "225300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019775180", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "30", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1580472000.0}
