{"text": "For 68 hours it might not be enough experience to know all the content in this game but I have enjoyed myself sincerely during those 68 hours. Ofcourse there were moments I was swearing my lungs out due to random bugs. Though this did not stop me from playing. Asfar as I have seen the developers they are very eager to listen to the community and listen to their critism. Besides that the whole game is build out of what players wanted which I personally think is an amazing concept and worked out concept with this game. The game has loads of options regarding what you will do, the things you can find or discover are endless and I gotta give it to these developers that they have created a game which can be calm, stressfull and sometimes even heart attackingly tense. I suggest this game to people who enjoy a sandbox like experience with an endless option of exploring. I rate this from personal enjoyment a 8.5/10.", "appid": "322780", "steamid": "profiles/76561198068017484", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1543233600.0}
