{"text": "See my review of the original game here.  Which still holds up! So I loved the original game so much, that when I got this remastered version for free for owning it, I had to play it to completion also. A lot of the issues that were wrong with the classic were fixed. Namely the tedious grind to just find the eggs in the first place. Now in this game, it's set up so you can only go so long before the game will just give you another egg. However it seems slightly harder to find the evolve items in this game, so it just becomes a time grind of getting all those to evolve the babies once you have them all. It's not so RNG as the first game though and easier. Still a rewarding and great experience to play this game. My only 2 complaints about this game is the voice acting for the cut scenes has been removed. And that there is no 100% completion achievement for getting all the stars on every hand. But they have said they may ad that achievement in the future.  If I'm being honest, I say get, play, and 100% both games!", "appid": "583930", "steamid": "profiles/76561198077644574", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567771200.0}
{"text": "I'll be honest, I don't play fighting games that often. The last fighting game I played was Mortal Kombat 4 way back when. I bought it on sale today and thought why not give it a go? So far I'm loving this game very much. It's a bit tough for me and I'm having a love/hate relation with it right now. For new players, you may wanna go and learn how this game plays or you're gonna get wrecked even on the easy difficulty, just like me! This game does a very poor job of explaining how it plays unless you've played the previous one. It's clearly not designed for new players. The graphics look well and it runs smoothly for me so far. Unless you use a controller, which I feel u should for this game, you'll break your keyboard after the first match lol. It's highly unresponsive for me until now and it's incredibly frustrating because I KNOW I'm pressing the right buttons at the right time. So I dunno, buy it on sale, I guess. Definitely not on full price.", "appid": "627270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198370866756", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574596800.0}
