{"text": "I have mostly positive things to say about Black Ops III. I surely do love BO3 to this day, and always will. I don't see as many hackers but people using controllers can be really annoying. I have been playing BO3 in the Middle East on European Servers and I would usually have a decent to terrible ping of 150-250 ms, where 150 ping is the best I have gotten. I believe Activision need to invest on dedicated servers in the Middle East/Asia because there are a majority of players in Asia that are forced to join EU servers and have their experience ruined from the terrible connection. As for the gameplay, I have little problems with the advanced movement in MP and the weapons feel very satisfying to use. Map design is overall good with my favorite maps being Nuk3town, Combine, Fringe, Outlaw, Skyjacked, Micro, Empire and several more. Graphics in BO3 could still hold up today, and it is fairly optimized for mid-range players. The soundtrack is also great, from SP, MP and Zombies. Treyarch did a really good job in this department. Zombies in BO3 is personally my favorite in the COD franchise. I'll just summarize my favorite maps here: - Shadows of Evil, a great map at launch. A visually appeasing map, and one of the most annoying mini-bosses of all time. And let's not all forget the ending cutscene on last gen... - Der Eisendrache, one of the greatest Zombies maps of all time. Awesome gameplay, overpowered Wonder Weapons, an intense boss fight and an easter egg cutscene that is very touching. I have actually visited the place of inspiration for Der Eisendrache which is in Werfen, Austria and I truly will never forget that moment. - Gorod Krovi, just like Der Eisendrache it remains as a top map among the players. Dragons and fire everywhere, another awesome easter egg and what is believed to be the last 'actual' map in the Aether story before Revelations. - And speaking of Revelations, a map that takes you across memory lane. Returning Wonder Weapons, a dope-looking Pack-a-Punch camo and probably one of the easiest maps in Zombies to go for high rounds. I think we should all appreciate that Treyarch then dropped Zombies Chronicles which then basically revolutionized CoD and some consider it the best game in the series, including me. Some Gobblegums in BO3 are too OP, but they are quite useful when speedrunning easter eggs or high rounds.  In here, I wanna talk about the Black Market. The Black Market is terrible, but I can say that BO4's adaptation is now miles better than BO3. All weapons are locked behind Supply Drops, old players will know about Triple Plays and how weapons could be earned for free. I had put a lot of money into BO3 (~$600) and despite the 'effort' I now have all weapons from the Black Market, and I promised myself not to spend another Dollar on a Supply Drop. I'm not gonna let the Black Market undermine my thoughts of BO3 because at the end of the day, I'm not gonna spend any more money on it. BO3 is just overall great. It's the most populated CoD on Steam and still is. It has been the longest supported CoD post-launch, mainly lasting for over 2 1/2 years which shows how much people truly play BO3. From my experience with Call of Duty: Black Ops III, you can theoretically expect endless playtime, however for some people that move on to different games can expect 500+ hours assuming that you are playing MP and ZM only. Definitely worth my purchase with over 2,000 hours on BO3. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Call of Duty: Black Ops 4 review: Guess I'll have to do my review here... Being Prestige Master in MP and ZM, this is a game that I have enjoyed despite some people's negative thoughts. I am now fully adapted to the MP and as a proud owner of Dark Matter on all modes, it definitely is one of my main achievements in my gaming career. Customization is now better than BO3 with awesome looking animated camos, outfits and weapon variants. But where do you get most of these? The Black Market! I suppose you didn't need to guess if you read my review of BO3.  But as I said in it, this Black Market is significantly better after November 12, 2019. This day marks the fact that Activision is making change to their monetization for future games. With the recent update to the Black Market, it will now be possible to obtain ALL items by grinding the game. 'All' as in previous items that could only be purchased. I believe this to be a huge win for all of us as I would have continued to keep on spending, and luckily enough I've only spend $250 in a single year (From April to October). I just don't know why this was implemented long before when Reserve Crates were introduced. But yeah, another year of grinding to completion. Blackout is indeed fun to play. My favorite limited time modes are Ambush, Alcatraz Portal and Hot Pursuit and Heavy Metal Heroes. I really enjoy stalking up to people and knifing them with the Bowie Knife! Never gets old... My only minor issue was that Blackout seemed to be getting more content than MP and ZM. I understand that Blackout is the pinnacle of BO4, however there has to be an equal amount of content added to all modes.  Speaking of modes, Zombies has somewhat changed from BO3. Some people say it is significantly harder than the previous game and I agree to a certain extent. The health system is weird and annoys me every time I go down. I am very glad that they added camo progression as soon even though it should have been on launch. And again, I got Dark Matter in Zombies since July 2019. Here's my verdict on my favorite Zombies maps in BO4: - Blood of the Dead, the remaster (or should I say re-imagine) of the fan-favorite Mob of the Dead. This is my most played map because it's very easy to set up and of course I know the map like the back of my palm. For some players, looking back at it now it seems to be a little bit disappointing on what was done, but I digress - IX, one of the most immersive maps I've played. Cheers everywhere, tigers in Rome and gladiators constantly coming for you. IX has a very simple map design and good graphics. - Classified, another reimagined map from \"Five\". My personal favorite map cuz it's another map that doesn't take long to set up and an easy camping spot. - Ancient Evil, a visually pleasing piece of art. Excellent gameplay and plenty of space to train zombies. Also the map takes place in Greece FTW ;) - Tag Der Toten, the last map in CoD Zombies as we say goodbye to our beloved characters. This may be a reimagining of Call of the Dead, but I feel that it looks/plays different to be its own unique map. I'm kinda sad that Treyarch confirmed that Operation Dark Divide will be their last major content drop in BO4 as they have moved onto Black Ops Cold War. Back in March 2018 Treyarch said that BO4 was supposed to last for years but promises do eventually break. I'll be taking a momentary break from BO4 as I've got no other choice than do delete it as it takes up too much space, and I find myself not coming to this game as often.", "appid": "311210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198333764689", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1527940800.0}
