{"text": "Overall its a great traditional ARPG without costing you a cent, deep, challenging and with a very dark ambience, but not for everyone.  Tons of RNG elements that makes you to trade items with non integrated trade system because, crafting is really pain in the ass. Story is very bad. Though it's not an unattractive game, Path of Exile doesn't have Torchlight 2's sense of style or Diablo 3's polish and yet, Its cosmetics are fairly expensive, with $30 getting you a pet, a soundtrack and 200 points. But how you choose to spend your money is your business. I really respect the idea of releasing a game like this without asking any money. This is really player friendly move and I have to give a huge credit to that. But, I wonder if this payment model works out for the developer Grinding Gear, if it's working out, it would be really good for them. I said PoE is a deep game, I didn't say that for nothig. Just the passive skill tree page might be enough to blow your mind and you may also see some people out there who have been playing this game more than 2000 hours but I must say, I'm not the fan of mindless farming and spamming every map to complete all achievements and get the best gear just to mindlessly farm more. I just dont see myself doing all this stuff again and again every season. Even though in every season they add new content to the game. And the game overall feels kinda outdated in 2020 so I'm going to wait for PoE 2 to come out and most probably I will play and finish the campaign in there too. Final Verdict:", "appid": "238960", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018764790", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600776000.0}
