{"text": "Monster Boy and the Cursed Kingdom took me right back to the old Super Nintendo days. This game is so much fun and there's a lot to do in it. It uses the style of all those classic platformers and takes advantage of new technology to make it such an awesome retro game. I like how they made the game a Metroidvania and you use all of monster boy's abilities and powers to move around the world. I felt like a kid again playing this game since it reminded me of when I used to play these kinda games back then. There are a lot of puzzles, there are some mini-games and they even added a side-scrolling shooter section just like the old games used to do! So I can say that this game is for everyone and if you have children, they are going to love it! I can't recommend this game enough and I think everyone that likes the Super Mario games and other classic games like that should really get this one, especially if you have kids!   I love this game! I like this game because you get to fight monsters and your powers stack up! You get to fight mini-bosses before you get to the actual boss fight. In some chests you find materials to craft weapons then once you find all of them you go to someone that crafts things for you and get new stuff from them. Before you fight a boss you can go to a store to refill your power-ups and health items. Sometimes there's a character that if you collect purple gems you get to upgrade your weapons before the boss. There are chests in different places like under water and sometimes you need to switch your character in order to get that chest. I like that you can turn into so many creatures and I like them all but my favorite one is the Dragon because he can fly, he could shoot fire and can also breath under water. All the characters have different special abilities that you need to use to go to different places. There are a lot of hidden rooms so you need to use all the different characters to get in them. I love that you can help others and go on quests to help them with what they need. I have my own save file too for me to play by myself and there are a lot of save slots if you have brothers and sisters and don't want to share your profile. I'm really happy I have this game and I think other kids are going to love it too!", "appid": "449610", "steamid": "profiles/76561198150434226", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "22", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569758400.0}
