{"text": "efined and rich in content, the best strategy game from the Star Wars universe, created by the masters of the genre - Ensemble Studios, under the care and support of LucasArts in full form and glory. he quickest and easiest way to sum up this game is \"Age of Empires II: The Age of the Kings\" in the Star Wars universe. And even though it reflects the state of affairs quite well, it is worth adding that this is not an ordinary and simple AoE II reskin, but a full-fledged title built on a proven foundation and developed, as much as the 'Genie Engine' allowed, to best reflect the spirit of the battles in this universe. Although the game did not get any refreshed, significantly improved version (which it deserves) except for a digital release, with the help of simple fan mods or patches it runs and looks great on modern systems - just like with AoE II gameplay and audiovisual setting have stood the test of time. or Star Wars fans, especially those brought up on classic strategies - a game not to be missed. At a low price, we get a product with ridiculously low system requirements, loaded with favorite factions, movie-related campaigns, map editor, AI skirmishes, multiplayer and everything else that the Age of Empires formula from the turn of the millennium offered. SWGB's biggest offense is that AoE II came out first and has managed to build a devoted fanbase around it, including the key to long-term success - the multiplayer community. Star Wars titles from the period of the Second Trilogy are of mixed quality. This game is definitely one of the most solid choices out there.", "appid": "356500", "steamid": "profiles/76561197988448796", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "25", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603627200.0}
