{"text": "My favorite platformers from the ps1 days are finally here beautifully remastered, and I am happy to say they did a great job!  The graphics are so well done, it was pretty much jaw dropping the first time I've seen it, it's very well done.  The main game however isn't perfect of course, not bad at all but there were some things that the original did better in terms of gameplay and overall detail(especially in the 2nd and 3rd game with its rich worlds with more characters in it). Some of these changes weren't necessarily worse or inferior all the time, just different. It was mostly kept the same.  The new soundtrack wasn't always on point for me, it was way too soft most of the time, thankfully they gave you the option to swap to the original soundtrack, which was a very good decision, Crash should've done the same.  The most effort was definitely put into the first game with the rescuable dragons now having their own unique looks instead of their copy and paste designs in the original, and they have more characteristics and sometimes even have new things to say.  The rest were done pretty well too despite their flaws or missteps, I did however encountered most of the glitches in the 3rd game, and even had a game breaking one which forced me to alt+f4 about 3 times in a row. They could've worked on these a little bit more.  Overall these game are still very nicely done, it was very good to revisit these classics once again. However if I would have to recommend this to those who have not played the originals before, I would say this might not be for you, especially nowdays with arguably better collectathon platformers on the market. But if you are really curious how it was back then, then I'd say give it a shot or wait for a price drop. I'm giving this an 8/10 - If it wasn't for my nostalgia then I would give it a 7/10 which still counts as a very good score in my book.", "appid": "996580", "steamid": "profiles/76561198091867267", "voted_up": true, "votes_u