{"text": "This game is such a gem. The gameplay alone makes it a worthwhile purchase, but the true beauty of this game is in the sound and design. The best way I can think to describe the music is that it's something reminiscent of Danny Elfman, Edward Scissorhands in particular. The narrator speaks to you on your journey, making for quite the immersive start and then some. The best thing has to be how this game makes you think - and I don't mean with puzzles, though it will certainly do that. I believe the game must be a metaphor for how small and insignificant humans feel on the Earth, and about trying to attain some sort of meaning. The void will always find you... 10/10", "appid": "252670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198083556847", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1430136000.0}
{"text": "Darkarta is one of the best Hidden Object Games I've ever played. It's made with great quality. The art is marvelously detailed and vivid. I had to take a screen shot of almost every scene since it's so mesmerizing. Game impresses you from start to finish. It's visible a lot of love and effort it's poured into this piece. Cut scenes are wonderful and done with care. Game has hours of content and it holds the attention very well. I especially loved totally new and innovative approach to puzzles and HO scene that I've never seen anywhere else before. You will not find repetitive puzzles through the same scene. The music was always spot on and beautiful to listen to. If you are an achievement hunter: some areas will become inaccessible so try to find all morphing objects and memories when you first enter the location. It was wonderful to experience this game because story is so heartwarming and deep. Story of love, sacrifice, revenge and karma.", "appid": "601530", "steamid": "profiles/76561198113243844", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594209600.0}
