{"text": "Awesome game! The game is just a song! I was in 2008, when I came out, I remember only that it was not easy there, to hell with the small Japanese who were constantly changing their positions in the sights, and their darkness, like cockroaches, from every slit. Now, in 2019, he's gone through it all in one breath.  Everything as we love! Even there are several missions for the Soviet Union: a sniper in Stalingrad, the Zeolov Heights in front of Berlin, a mission in a tank battalion on the T-34 - a tense one, because they beat on us from all sides. The extermination of fascists in the streets of Berlin to patriotic music is a song! Assault of Reistag! For americans it is also fantastic. The Japanese are endless waves of attacks. A couple of places had to die a dozen times. Burning the enemy with a flamethrower in the trenches, unexpected snipers on the palm trees around you, kills with one grenade, if you think about it and in 2 seconds did not have time to escape.  Missions are long.  Russian voice - often rusty to \"I can't laugh\")))) Separate comedy In this series of CoDa -- War with a capital letter. Minuses: Allied inscriptions constantly climb on the line of your fire. Plus: I love to shoot single-handedly with a rifle, and here the rifle is the main weapon. 9 Japanese kamikaze out of 10", "appid": "10090", "steamid": "profiles/76561198828107633", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1567339200.0}
