{"text": "Old Man's Journey is a short lighthearted (  point & click/puzzle game.  Since the game can be completed within 2 hours and you probably finish the game in one sitting, whether or not you like the game really depends on the mood at the time of playing. Personally I think this is a nice game to play on a sunday morning. First of all I think the graphics are nice and creative. The music and sounds did their part, nothing bad but nothing special either.  There is no narration in this game, so you have to piece the story together by what you see and I think this is done pretty well for the most part, although it does leave some questions;  The gameplay mainly consists of clicking through the world and make grandpa walk around. You can click on other things in the world but this is all very minimal; For example you can click on doors to open just for fun. The puzzles consist mainly of terraforming the country/hills so grandpa can walk over them, sometimes sheep are standing in your way so you have to find a way around them. The puzzles were not extremely hard but I did encounter some bugs where I could not continue because I did the puzzle not the way it was intended.  I would say Old Man's Journey is a nice game to play one time.", "appid": "581270", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970064749", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591704000.0}
