{"text": "ps. Thai lang below the eng review !! I think the first 500h could be interesting, until you reach the endless grinding state, after that it is just boring, you cant pvp without putting a lot of work into grinding, and then comes the rng for enhancing. You can spent an absurd amount of your time in this game... I have 2300h+ and i think 2000h+ of this is afk time (there is a ton of afk things you can do to earn money, playing the actively will result in much faster gear progression, obviously....) For 10 euro/dollar, / 200 Baht i recommend this game. Pvp 6/10: Cons: Not balanced, doesnt require any skill, gear dependant, heavy d-sync, class carried, not interesting battleground, large scale pvp = lagfest Pros: Non-target, cool animation, interesting combos, fast paced Conclusion: Pvp is interesting if you have friends to fight against, and after you reach the minimum required gear to do it. Until then, dont even bother... Pve 6/10: Cons: Repetitive, boring, no dungeons, no raids, basically an offline game Pros: A big variation in grinding spots, till you reach endgame Lifeskills ?/10: Never tried, wasnt interested, but there is a large variety of lifeskills you can do, like gathering, fishing, alchemy, cooking, sailing, etc. Graphics 9/10: Best visuals i have ever seen in an MMORPG, can be glichy sometimes in certain areas... Gameplay 9/10 before it gets boring, after its a 6/10... Overall 7/10 (sorry for bad english) ---{Graphics}--- ☐ You forget what reality is ☑ Beautiful ☐ Good ☐ Decent ☐ Bad ☐ Don‘t look too long at it ☐ Paint.exe ---{Gameplay}--- ☑ Very good ☐ Good ☐ It‘s just gameplay ☐ Mehh ☐ Starring at walls is better ☐ Just don‘t ---{Audio}--- ☐ Eargasm ☑ Very good ☐ Good ☐ Not too bad ☐ Bad ☐ Earrape ---{Audience}--- ☐ Kids ☑ Teens ☑ Adults ☐ Salty people ☐ Human ☑ Weebos ---{PC Requirements}--- ☐ Check if you can run paint ☐ Potato ☑ Decent ☑ Fast ☐ Rich boiiiiii ☐ Ask NASA if they have a spare computer ---{Difficulity}--- ☐ Just press ‚A‘ ☐ E