{"text": "TLDR: Criware & Unreal Engine 4 had  a baby, thanks to BANDAI NAMCO I played one of the earlier soul caliburs on play station 1 around 2005 , so, i know of the background, never paid attention then except for knowing all the characters were armed with their weapons, This game kicks off in the 1600's - 1584/86 or something like this, and it's about the dual-wielding pirate that carried the blades of chaos. The one shattered but the evil parts ripped and shattered in to the world via the ocean, and where it has gone, astral planes have started opening up, and turning people into malphesants, or if they can overcome the chaos powers, they are usually stronger.. You level up after your scenario fights, and travel the worldmap, with a story intro to where you are going, or need to go, and then the fight takes place, after cinematic [Skippable] Bladed Fighting weapons are the fighting specialisms that this fighting game covers. It's great, make your own character :Libra mode to play your own sick fate, or help the chaotic universe that wants to devour your soul.  But your own character can swap out their weapon each time on the worldmap, in preparation for the fights, Really cool - relaxing background music, and the world map reminds me a lot of Game of Thrones™ - Very nice and detailed, - but it's of our Earthly- world map - so it's relatable, and really cool {ie. fight to stay alive} And the other modes of  Default resolution scale was at like 85% or something, so check this if you buy it,  Since playing a PS1 game to now, the graphics have obviously improved last i remember it. The criware + UE4 love is apparent. Fighting mechanics are okay, but you CANNOT kick or punch people through the walls, like other fighting games, [i kicked someone off the cliff in my first fight - and there was an invisible wall] , but your head can be backhanded into the wall. It's really good, the hitboxes are all over the body and the characters react based on where you are striking them, Extremely animated fights, super responsive, but sometimes you can let loose a combo, and it  plays out after you stop pressing buttons,  Still good and smooth the first hour in -let's see how it goes -> The price is always hefty with BANDAI NAMCO< but the replayability can be longer than most games. Will try cover an update on internet -> to europe from South Africa, for Online matches. Videos, cinematics and animations look so crisp, DLC's involve characters and more decoration, not interested with so little play time yet", "appid": "544750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019159426", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601640000.0}
