{"text": "+ Compelling mystery +  Interesting and realistic characters + Looks great and runs well - Occasionally unnatural conversations - Underwhelming ending Story-driven video games have always been some of my favorite, regardless of the format they are presented in. They often tackle subjects that other games simply do not have the capacity to do so, given their more complex approach to storytelling and such. So of course I was interested in Tell Me Why, even if I have yet to play the studio’s past works. Tell Me Why is yet another example of proper storytelling in video game form. It boasts a compelling mystery, a cast of interesting and realistic characters, and also looks great on top of that while running well on modern hardware. As someone that plays a ton of story-driven games, I can definitely say it’s worth a look, even if the ending may have been unsatisfying. Follow my   for more reviews + videos!", "appid": "1180660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028020795", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602504000.0}
