{"text": "This game can get you attached QUICKLY. Its really fun to fight and defend your own colony and raid other colonys, and when  a colonist dies you become very sad becuase of your grown attachment to them. The building in the game is also very simple but you can get VERY creative with it. Every colonist counts too even if one cant do much of anything but is REALLY good at something, you still need to keep them, they may be the one to keep your colony going. You willget random things happen at random times such as beavers who want to come and eat every tree or your house catching on fire from a wire breaking, the randomness goes from things breaking and needing to be repaired, to hundreds upon hundred of people coming to raid your colony. While playing this game its easy to forget what time it is or how long you have been playing for because it is so addicting i personally have about 400 hours when making this review. There is much more to Rimworld but I wouldnt want to spoil it for you.", "appid": "294100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198208172823", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1532433600.0}
