{"text": "a solid improvement from Just Cause 3, which was an improvement from Just Cause 2.   first, the bad: -controls are hard to get used to -menu system is extremely confusing at first, hard to get used to -some vehicles still suck.  atvs and bikes specifically are still toxic garbage to control.  boats are still a tad odd but not as bad as Just Cause 3 next, the good: - improved visual -lush forests, feel full and beautiful - GREATLY improved control on wingsuit, parasuit and grapple, thumbs up -challenges are short and sweet, but fun and take you to cool places.  -improved weapon combat and feel.  combat feels good.  melee GREATLY improved, more like Just Cause 2. the epic (things that stuck out as super cool): --- grapple mod customization     --you can make them automatically activate or to a tap or hold of a button which is great         -you can stack these with other mods to create nicely handling grapple mods     --there is a cross grid that lets you amplify your mods in other ways to create even more unique customizations --- weapons  have awesome unique firing modes.  I love the light machine gun that opens up into a personal barrier with the gun mounted, so freakin cool --- lots of wild unique vehicles, the flying car, the aquatic car the land boat that shoots all over. this was fun.", "appid": "517630", "steamid": "profiles/76561198005657392", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605614400.0}
