{"text": "Square Enix and Crystal Dynamics are putting their own spin on the classic Marvel heroes in Marvel's Avengers. Let's kick this review off with the multiplayer. The game features   which is a massive post-campaign online adventure for four players to complete. Many of these missions require you to have a high power level and because of that, it is highly recommended not to begin   until you finish the main story. The thing with multiplayer is that it's really great...(when it works XD). There's a whole bunch of bugs which, fortunately, developers are aware of and are working on fixing them. Matchmaking sadly, seems to be broken most of the time. At first, it wouldn't work at all, then it would matchmake you with 1 person instead of 3. Now I honestly have no idea whether or not it has improved since the last time I tried it because I haven't tried to find a game since then. When it comes to campaign, I very seldom follow the story in online games and usually just rush to the endgame but, I have to admit, this one really intrigued me. I don't know why but I was having a blast going through the campaign. It was really interesting and I always wanted to play another mission. Obviously the plot is not nearly as good as The Last Of Us for example but it does not change the fact that it is really fun and enjoyable gaming experience(especially for Marvel's Avengers universe fan). + Great Story Campaign + Solid and Satisfying Combat System + An Abundance of Potential For Growth + Decent Replayability(which kinda connects to the previously mentioned advantage) + Aesthetically Pleasing Visuals - Bugs and Performance Issues(which are going to be fixed very soon though) - Level Design(only a few different open warzone areas shared between missions) - Repetitive Gameplay(which kinda connects to Level Design to some degree) - Balancing Issues", "appid": "997070", "steamid": "profiles/76561198041644181", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599739200.0}
