{"text": "Oh man what could I say about Disco Elysium. \"Don't worry about how it ends, worry about how you'll get there.\" This is the RPG I've been looking for and frankly my GOTY, I haven't found anything like this since Arcanum, Divinity and Tyranny, I know there are others but those are my tops. This game is dialog rich/heavy, you'll be doing a lot of reading, you'll want to skip past it all, but you really gotta pay attention. Your character already has a predetermined history, but its up to you to change how people perceive him or just make things worst, or crazy wacky hilarious. Either way I can say this is the first game thats actually made me \"lol\" reading the text, multiple times. It has its slow moments, and the typical mistakes great games with great writing makes. But its definitely worth it if you're already thinking about it, why not give it a try and become a superstar cop.", "appid": "632470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198012209211", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574769600.0}
