{"text": "Finished the entire game in about four hours. Upon starting the game, Orwell immediately draws you in with the unique and interesting mechanics. It reminds me vaguely of text adventures/CYOA games but with more graphics and interactions. The story is excellent and I found myself wondering what happens next.  It gives you a lot to think about and I definitely questioned my morals at one point in the game. All in all, a wonderfully crafted game well worth your money. My only complaint is that there is no way to fast forward chat logs/calls and it can be a little slow sometimes. There's no way to get all achievements without replaying and I find myself wondering what would've happened if I'd chosen a little differently. 11/10 would play again.", "appid": "491950", "steamid": "profiles/76561198802638239", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1557576000.0}
