{"text": "Hellblade is truly a fascinating game and close to a masterpiece of artist gaming. The game is bleak and touches on a very sensitive subject using metaphors and visual complexity to drive home its message.  Visually Hellblade is stunning, the environments are lush and its desolate surroundings is your only companion throughout, the facial animation is immaculate and the actress portraying the lead is not your typical beauty but feels like a real person. The actress needs to be commend on her great performance and her tortured nature really comes through. Voice acting is also outstanding with a host of voice constantly bombarding you through out your journey to really drive home the torment. It is the voices that is a truly great design choice not only are they a tool in which to demonstrate your psychosis they are also your in game guide during traversal and combat. You see you have no hud and they act as your compass as well as you warnings of incoming attacks. In fact not in any other game has sound been so integral to the experience than here, where some situations your hearing is more important than your visual. Gameplay consists of puzzle solving and combat scenarios, first the combat which is so satisfactory in execution, there is weight to strikes and its methodical opposed glorified techniques, with each slash feeling powerful. The biggest problem that can be attributed to the combat is that sometimes it can be a test of endurance with some enemies taking a bit too long to kill or that there are just too many waves of enemies. Then we have the puzzles which are very creative in which you have to analysis your surroundings and match symbols or view areas from a different perspective. The puzzles are challenging enough and never over stay there welcome. The balance of combat and puzzles are well implemented.  Movement can feel sluggish at times especially for traversal where your run is nothing but a mild jog. Environments are detailed but nothing is interactive and there is a host of invisible walls to funnel you on the one and only path. The game is strictly linear and for me sometimes linear is good. Sadly the game is not particularly long and there is not much in the form of replay value other than for the experience again. There is not much in the form of side content and no chapter select to relive certain areas. I really do recommend this game for adventurers and people who love great combat, puzzles and character pieces.", "appid": "414340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116446104", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593259200.0}
