{"text": "There is a really good game to be made here i personally like every thing about this game and can not wait for the full installment.  Controls/game-play  : 10/10 Simple but a real joy to play they work as they should, the sword play is really something to behold and the special moves are really fun to mess with excluding Sanyati's which is not needed other than to get to high ledges (honestly I wouldn't have it any other way DO NOT CHANGE), only problem or complaint I have about them is the wall jumps are a bit hard to do sometimes, but that's probably just that my timing's off. It has a very Hotline Miami feel like every death is death is your fault, it makes you (or at least me want to jump back in as soon as possible), also no need to worry because there's a \"checkpoint\" as soon as you enter the next room. Sure there's some bugs but its just a pilot so it gets a pass on that.   Story: 10/10 Besides trying to take over the grey area/district which will be fun on its own, there's more to the story or at least I hope from the (room) you can find with the like 5 messages or so. Interaction: 10/10 Dialogue is funny but not over the top, its got a few memes in the dialogue and on secret but you activate it via talking to a NPC so I will count it here there's like 3-4 memes in the game, but their not in your face about it. At least I thought so.   Music: 10/10 I couldn't get enough of these killer tracks. Visuals: 10/10 Pixel art its phenomenal, reminds me of Hotline Miami, with holding its own identity.  The only main thing I will rip on is how you select the characters : Sanyati or Zambezi. Then play as Sanyati mostly you can only play as Zambezi two times. I hope this implies multiplayer or we can change characters for missions to get different dialogue like when you challenge the first gang.  Point being its a fantastic game that should be enjoyed by all and i mean all. 10/10 once again I absolutely can't wait to get my hands on the full game.  I can harp about other things about this game all day, but rather just you go and play it yourself and experience the treat that this game is.", "appid": "1178030", "steamid": "profiles/76561198336402984", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1579780800.0}
