{"text": "All good things come in threes, that's how the idiom goes and it is most certainly true for the third installment of the   series. I was already highly excited to play through it, but yet again, my expectations were surpassed at every corner.  keeps all the core mechanics from its predecessor, i.e. interaction with the environment, progression through the game etc. However, it expands on these elements by introducing a larger scale with more dynamic, increasingly difficult, but similar puzzle types the further along you progress and an overall much more intricate design. You won't progress linearly anymore, but rather branch out from a central hub to explore different locations that all contribute to your ultimate goal.  Utilizing small cutscenes and the well-known letters you find scattered around, the player will be able to familiarize themselves even more with what they are actually solving all these puzzles for. Again, the story does not play a great role in the game, so even players who don't care for story much will be able to find great enjoyment in  I recommend reading my previous reviews, because it is difficult to praise something again without repeating myself. Every game in the   series has astonished me with the beautiful visuals and the wonderful, almost surreally fitting nature of the ambience noise and sounds. Combined they give the game an uneasy, yet somehow almost relaxing vibe which will keep you on edge even though you know there are no jumpscares. I can only say what I said before: The   series is a fantastic adaptation of the point-and-click escape the room genre that will keep you wanting to explore further until you reach the very end. I can guarantee that the even the third installment will not feel like a remake of the previous games at all, but will present you with a completely new, unique and well-crafted experience that you will find yourself wanting to see through all the way, and maybe even again.", "appid": "456750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198116637933", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "21", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1561809600.0}
