{"text": "I would rate this game as neutral if I could.  This is my first Monster Hunter game.  At first I wasn't too impressed. There was a lot of connectivity issues and overall I do still think that the online multiplayer is needlessly tedious and annoying at times due to cutscenes that are required to be seen before you can join someone else's quest or someone else joins yours. (This is only for new quests not done yet, story mode stuff.) I just wish that it was a lot easier to party up with people and be together all of the time instead of having to party up, disband, party up again, disband, over and over and over again. Also, randoms can be very good or very stupid. It's definitely best to play in a party of four with your friends rather than relying on randoms.  Pros: - the graphics are awesome - the sound is very good as well - pretty 'epic' fights - large variety of weapons to use for lots of different play styles - game runs quite smooth if you have the hardware to run it properly - Palicos are super cute - it's cool to see two or more monsters fighting each other - the game seems pretty well optimized for PC, but then again I use a controller - no mandatory day one DLC crap necessary to enjoy the game Cons: - the game is very grindy, so if grinding out materials isn't your thing, this game isn't for you because you WILL spend a lot of time doing the same things over and over and over again - many things in the game are not explained very well - while the combat isn't terrible, it's not good either... you basically just do the same things over and over while rolling / dodging  - huge leap in difficulty after you hit high rank - playing solo feels really boring, at least for me... although it seems far easier than playing multiplayer  -monster AI sometimes doesn't make any sense -normal \"aggro\" systems in most games is totally different in this game -having to sharpen weapons in battle (even hammers!) is annoying and stupid -the amount of time it takes to use items in battle - like potions, etc - is ridiculous and often leads to deaths -some game mechanics feel way more random than they should be, like mounting monsters -unless you grind a lot, you're never going to have enough money or materials to craft what you need - the storyline is stupid, but who really cares? - while \"friendly fire\" isn't on in the sense that you can damage each other, friendly hits do often cancel your own attacks and bring you out of a charged attack, which is super annoying, especially with 4 players - damage seems inconsistent. sometimes you take very little damage and other times you can get hit with something that kills you in one shot if you're not at max HP.  - many weapons feel very slow and it is quite easy to miss a LOT of attacks - getting stunned/dazed lasts a long time and can easily result in you getting killed - always running out of stamina gets really annoying - enemy monsters are damage sponges that have what seems to be a billion HP  - without resorting to the internet for information, it can be very hard to find certain items or to unlock certain quests because you get little to no info in the game - lots of \"Leeroy Jenkins\" type people in multiplayer - monsters always running away in battle and having to chase after them several times gets annoying AF - you can't cancel certain attacks in the middle of attacking and instead of have to watch and wait as your character swings their weapon around like a ♥♥♥♥♥♥ and the animation is finished - not being able to do certain things multiplayer, like go on Grimalkyne quests and whatnot (the stuff only shows up for the party leader) - can't quickly and easily join hosted quests/optionals/events with a friend... you basically HAVE TO chat and both join the same thing at the same time, hopefully before the player list fills up - always being low on money (crafting higher rank gear and weapons costs a ton of money) - the Melder makes no sense at all Overall I'd say that there's a bunch of annoying aspects of the game (IMHO) but overall the game isn't bad, but the bad/annoying aspects of it outweigh the good. If you're into grindy cooperative stuff and have 3 friends to play with and don't mind using the internet for info so you can powerlevel your way through the game and grind out all your materials, it's not so bad.", "appid": "582010", "steamid": "profiles/76561198029579963", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1535112000.0}
