{"text": "PC; Win 10 64-bit; Trapped Dead v1.1.0.0 uncompleted; playing time: 3 hrs Pros: + an interesting beginning of the game at the gas station, promising an engrossing continuation + noteworthy mechanics of presenting the stages of the plot  Cons: - controls are rather annoying; you have to use the keyboard to move the camera - there are no settings - no audio or video settings..., nothing... - most importantly, the game won't run; I tried to run it several times and most of the times it wouldn't run; I managed to only run it twice - above all, Trapped Dead caused my computer to   several times; this is the first time that any game on Steam has done so, which makes it worthy of a negative review... All in all, I suggest avoiding this game. Although the setting and the presentation seem interesting (provided you actually manage to run the game), Trapped Dead clearly suffers from serious technical problems which go far beyond its pesky controls or even lack of any settings. Due to the risk of accidental resets, it is likely to be dangerous to your computer, putting your computer file integrity at risk. It's a crying shame as, in my opinion, the game has got great potential...", "appid": "46540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078618048", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1451736000.0}
