{"text": "Pinstripe is a game with cute graphics, There we go we just invalidated over 90% of the positive review the game has because all of them will hyperfocus on that one part of the game while completely ignoring everything else. What do I mean by that? Well, lets see. What I'm writing will just be echoed by all the other review. I'm just writing this to get it out of my head. First, cute graphic. We touched on that. Next. The audio, standard wishy washy music thingy that's utterly forgetteable.  Voice acting, there's like 10 lines of dialogue for everyone so while one of the character sound genuinely depressed and tired, that's about it really.  Gameplay. Biggest meh.  It was probably made for children. The puzzles requires the barest amount of thoughts to get through, 3 of them aren't even puzzle but just 'find the words to unlock the stuff that we placed conveniently in plain sigh' and 4 of the mini-games are literally just reflex test with one of the minigame used only once then utterly forgotten. We even have variation of flappy bird gameplay of all things. The game only nominally have 30 min of actual gameplay, what about the other 1:30 hours? Well that's just there as padding so you can't refund the game on time if you take even the slightest amount of detour. 40 of those minutes were going back every single area of the first part just to burn away fungus or whatever to collect enough money to buy a ticket so you can access the cable car with the password at the back of the ticket.  The password don't work until you buy the ticket. I actually went online to find the combination because the mere thought of   padding through the entirety of the first area again is enough to give me migraine over how boring and pointless it is. And surprise, the code doesn't work naturally.  The game feels horrendously stapled together with its bunch of minigames having no explanation or rhythm to it. It has 3 enemy types, and 1 of them is just a reskinned tougher version of the other. Money plays absolutedly no role besides gatekeeping that part of the game until you collected enough as well. The story is even worse. You a priest vs some guy named pinstripe who kidnaps your daughter and now you have to go on a quest to save her. A quest that takes a maximum of 2 hours.  Pinstripe motivation was never explained, the ending was supremely abrupt and again explains nothing, 3 of the character exist just to give you stuff while claiming to help you [but not really they don't actually do anything.] and the relationship between them and the main character is never explained nor explored.   Would I recommend it? No. I got it in a bundle and the sensation that I had just wasted money and my time playing it never really quite left me. For the price they normally demand? Hhahaha. F*uck it just save your money and get an indie game that has more gameplay value than this. If you still want the feeling the game tries to invoke within you with its slapdash story, just play this 5 minute free game about a fly flying around. Anyone with a shred of empathy will feel wayyyyy more deeply about their feelings playing The Plan over Pinstripe.", "appid": "331480", "steamid": "profiles/76561198068929225", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589198400.0}
{"text": "H1Z1 Timeline: Early Access game Released on Jan 15, 2015 for $20. (Keep this in mind.) People loved it, and it got support. (Sidenote: It goes all downhill from here. Yea. Pretty quick right?) Devs made their BR mode a higher priority instead of their main survival mode (You know, the main draw to the game? Yea. Pretty smart right?) Fast foward. In October 2017, the Devs split the one game into two separate games. (Sure! just split the playerbase in half! they'll still support us! Also, lets make each game $20 while we're at it so we can maybe make more money off this quickly dying game!) Devs rebrand both games so many times it's hard to keep track. (Great for marketing btw). Both games suffered from less people working on them due to less people working on them. Daybreak gives up with communicating with their community. (The only people who still like their game). Games such as Fortnite and PUBG came out which took almost every person away from H1Z1. Daybreak came to the conclusion that they were dying. So what do they do? On February 28, 2018, they made the $20 game, that so many people bought, free. Oh, you thought that's where it ended? yikes! you won't like what you read next. August 24, 2018, the devs for the game \"Just Survive\" (THE ORIGINAL GAME) announce that the game will be discontinued and taken off of steam. The game was never finished and is still in early access. Also, I can't get my refund. FInal Words: I supported Daybreak by purchasing their $20 game. It got split to make more money. One of the games became free, which makes me feel I got scammed. And to top all off, the original game mode is now discontinued and I can't play it even if I wanted to. I paid $20 for actually nothing. Seriously. Never buying a game from Daybreak again. Also, did I mention I can't get refund?", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198434122094", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "550", "votes_funny": "68", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1537617600.0}
{"text": "An awful Garry's Mod clone. The bad case of trying to copy-paste the Gmod interface and gameplay, but in UE4 and absolutely with no content. You'll not get any new features, physical innovations or something. You also aren't getting all basical stuff and features that Garry's Mod includes. There are just a couple of basic props, vehicles and NPC's with pretty bad animations and AI. It's pretty far even from the basic Gmod without mods. This game is poor alpha at fact, as if another guy wants to tell us \"Hey look, how beautiful Gmod could be\". But after all this is on the release state. Do not waste your money for another \"UE4 features demonstration\". It doesn't worth even 3$, it should be in closed alpha test or free to play. But not the finished product.", "appid": "1127460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198058914683", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "46", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1587643200.0}
