{"text": "My thoughts of the game so far. Pros- Better combat system better towers Bigger tavern Better graphics Better player level system Cons- Key layout Cashshop class slots cost real money Tavern setup its everyone in one tavern Bigger bag cost real money costumes cost real money loot boxes cost real money to unlock No trading system Yes i get with a f2p game they need money in order to keep the game going such as every thing costing real money to get. I think if they added things from first game it could be alot better. I don't like haven't buy class slots or costumes. In dungeon defenders one they gave you 12+ class slots all free you didnt have to buy any thing with real money but big dlcs with came with hoilday quest, more story mission more items, costumes, challanges and the most was 20 dollars. I just feel like they are missing some of the best from from the other two games.Its not all bad they have improved alot of things but with some of the best stuff missing from the other games. They also took out offline so you must have internet to play. There is also a lack of towers from the first game, now when i say that what i mean is they took out some of the towers from the first game wich i don't know why all towers were used and needed for the first one. DLC: parts from the first game was you did have to buy it but as i said before it came with alot of added stuff. Now if you want somthing that looks cool you have to buy gems (real money) . In the first one in order to get cool costumes, weapons or even pets you had to beat a challange or a level on normally a high difficulty. I feel from that there was some pride when you get it cause it shows you went through alot to get it. Now you can just buy it me personally i would rather earn it. Tavern: I liked the way that had it setup where you there was a list of matches. So you can see all the matches being played. You could host your own tavern. But with that there are pros and cons from that like from people hosting there own matches they could kick you if they wanted but with that its also good for it people arent helping or causing problems. Also with having taverns you could set out the items you've gotten from your troubles of hard work for trades like if you're looking for a weapon but cant get you could trade for it with money, weapons, armor and even pets. Also i just remembered that the trophies you unlocked were setup in the tavern to show what you've completed. That helps people know if you can help them with a challange or with a very challanging match. Class slots: They only give you 4 class slots which i think is **** compared to what they had in the first one 12+ class slots Which allowed you to make  tower and dps classes instead of one or the other but with that being said in the first one they did have more classes to choose from instead of the base four.  THIS REVIEW WILL BE CHANGED AND UPDATED THE MORE I PLAY THE GAME AND IT GETS UPDATE CHANGES TO THE GAME.", "appid": "236110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198073785387", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1448798400.0}
{"text": "Un jeux fps génial. Il s'agit d'un jeux parallele a Battlefield. Ce jeux a un potentiel.  Malheureusement, le reste est a revoir: -prix des armes trop trop cher -Les viseurs encore pire -Pas assez de piece apres chaque parti gagner -Le vip ? Pay to win (Magasin a fric). Juste pour gagner des skin a 2 balle -Bug ? Beaucoup trop de beugue, surtotu au niveau de la map. Les armes sont un peu mal foutu.  -Je sais pas si il y a des cheater mais le gars qui me fous une balle avec l'arme de base (j ai des gros doutes...) -Ou sont les voitures dans le trealer ? Je sais que le jeux est sorti en mars, mais il perd toute sa communauté. Apres 10h de jeux, je vais le laisser tomber en attendant de nouvelle maj... C'ets pas un jeux difficile a faire car c'ests ur unreal engine et le pire ets que ce sont des asset acheter... Preuve, aller dans le marché unreal engine, vous verrez les meme asset. C'est juste un jeux gagné, pay to win. Bon je peux pas, mais si ils abbandonnent, j'achete le jeux pour le renover.", "appid": "1241100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198333060618", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1592222400.0}
