{"text": "DO NOT SPEND YOUR MONEY. In the same way a lack of planning doesn't constitute an emergency on someone else's part, Crema's lack of foresight re: loopholed coding does not constitute a non-refunded mass banning of significant % of playerbase. Bans delivered en masse for non-maliciously employing game functions as intended. Poor coding, poor business, poor execution. Recommend sticking to Pokémon/avoiding this developer. 900+ bans and counting, no option for appeal, all due to players using their hard-coded included game functions as intended; most without even an explanation as to their perma ban receipt. SKIP THIS GAME. Devs are dirty biz. If you choose to invest your time and money anyway -- simply be aware that the Devs can and have nullified that investment for ~1,000+ paying consumers. Frankly, the whole scenario reeks of an unethical tactic to fund their initially overwhelmed servers. I cannot in good faith recommend anyone give these developers their money unless you're silly enough not to care if it buys you continued/access to a game for your investment.", "appid": "745920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030736442", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "52", "votes_funny": "13", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1587902400.0}
