{"text": "Apparently, I’ve been waiting 6 years for… this. I’ve discovered Totono back in 2013-2014, soon after its initial release in Japan. Nitro+, meta elements, spookiness and yandere going total crazy were things that peaked my interest. Of course, I didn’t know Japanese, so considered waiting until there would be an English release. Luckily, it’s finally happened. I’ve booted the game expecting a mix of Yume Miru Kusuri with standard Nitro+ horror story elements. Well, at first it, certainly, was like this: your average protagonist, love interest 1 who’s perfect on the outside but has flaws deep inside, love interest 2 who’s weird and denpa but is actually sweet in her own way and, of course, is also a damsel in distress... Unfortunately, slice-of-life drama with meta elements I was expecting soon turned out to be just an average meta game with weak characters’ development and very boring and simple storyline. Just two girls, being aware they’re VN’s love interests and fighting over your affection, doing some crazy and yucky stuff. Obviously, because the narrative is centered around this topic, everything else becomes obscure and undeveloped – even side characters, like Haru and Yuutarou, soon turn into soulless puppets or decorative objects. Well, at least puzzles are entertaining, because the rest is a boring and pretty much linear mess.", "appid": "1293820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144117226", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592136000.0}
