{"text": "In one sentence, TBW is not what I really expected. The premise is actually great, ARG-style puzzle game where you browse through various piece of data, uncovering clues and answers to the mystery you're about to solve. Works great on paper, is awfully executed in this game. The game is not engaging, and puzzles are either too easy or too hard, no middle ground. There is no real game content, you're just given data pieces uploaded on TBW server and you're supposed to enter the answer the game is asking you to. Initially I loved that concept, the puzzles were really intriguing and well-made, there was even a website where I've \"ordered\" bunch of meds only to discover the name of the substance I was looking for - I mean, it shows the effort the devs made, the initial puzzles are gold, but it quickly deteriorates into complete crap where it's actually impossible to move on, either you're a dev who made the puzzle himself, or you'll go online searching for clues and then get angry at yourself, not because you were too stupid to find it out on your own, but because of how awful the puzzle was to begin with. This situation repeated itself around 2-3 times in a row for me, and I just lost any remaining willing to continue playing. I'm not exactly a stupid person, I love having those \"wait, could it be THAT\" moments in puzzlers where it requires me to actually use my brain, not bruteforce over 100 possible password combinations only because the game >expects< you to do, it's not puzzle-solving, it's not ARG, it's dumb bruteforcing a puzzle that doesn't have a working solution, where there is no right answer, but the answer the dev selected from 100 possible ones you're expected to try for yourself. If you're looking for ARG experience and you're having fun from spending several hours bruteforcing answers without any real idea what are you doing, then asking people on forum for help because the puzzles are impossible to solve on their own, go ahead, the game might be just for you. For me, a game which is realistically impossible to solve, telling me ITSELF to look for solutions ONLINE, is one huge mistake as user experience. Maybe I'm just too stupid for this game, but judging from experience of other people, I'm not in a minority. And I'm actually sad due to that, because I really wanted to like this game, the beginning was great, but it was ruined quickly enough with lack of good idea for future puzzles, it was simply too much of a burden to go through, and it got only worse the more I lied to myself that \"the next puzzle will surely be more interesting\". Personally, I do not recommend this game, Alice&Smith made at least one other game I've greatly enjoyed - NITE 4, but this one is a huge disappointment in my opinion.", "appid": "349220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006963719", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1592827200.0}
