{"text": "Current Review: Don't bother. Somehow this game became -worse- over time, riddled with bugs, places to get stuck in, low population, delayed key inputs and some of the most atrocious use of the english language I've ever seen. I can no longer recommend this game in it's state, and considering it's last updates were a few months ago, I'm pretty sure the game is dead in the water. First Review: Honestly? I love this game. Of course it has bugs and minor glitches, but what early access game doesn't? Even if it was released far from being complete, it has still got all its potential and more to go on. As of right now, I have been playing this game every hour that I can, and have not enjoyed it any less. I've met asshats and great people. I've been apart of communities, I've helped communities. I was really hyped for this game, following it back in January, so I was SO hyped to hear it was coming out. I bought it within seconds of that green button showing up so I could buy it. (Even worked my ass off the day prior to make sure I had the funds to pay for it.) No regrets. Not one. TLDR; if you can bare with the few teething issues, this game really is worth trying out.", "appid": "529180", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078772964", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1500724800.0}
