{"text": "I cant recommend this game as it has an achievement for being in early access meaning nobody who got the game after early access can 100% it.  I refused to buy it then got it for free when codemasters did a giveaway.  The game is okay but there is quite a lot of glaringly obvious problems.  Such as the start gates being misaligned and having rigid immovable flags and banners that if you drive forwards from the start line you crash into it leaving you to drive around it from the start line.  The championship mode is clunky and not fun, for some reason you can lead all the way through a championship then magically the AI is 20 seconds faster on the final stage like it is faked results.  The crew options are useless.  You will probably get annoyed restarting the same rally track over and over and over and over and over and over until you get mad and play a different game. There is a problem with the automatic gears when I use my gamepad as under heavy breaking it selects gear 1 and locks up the wheels skidding you out and losing you time and there is moments when it seems to be stuck in neutral and wont select a gear.  the replay system is nice with its slow mo.  If this didnt have the broken achievements I would recommend it.  Has some nice cars in it and some of the courses are good fun.  The graphics and physics are nice and you can trim down the UI so there is nothing on screen which is a good plus.", "appid": "310560", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970961386", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575547200.0}
