{"text": "No Man's Sky I have played the game for a good amount of time now and I am going to start with saying. This game is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ awesome. First time I started the game I am fly through the systems and I crash in an random Planet. Sadly I wanted to change my Grafix so I put the most on high and I noticed fps was on 30 so I put it  on Max. It needed a restart when I restated the game and come back to play this awesome game I was in another random planet where I started my journey. I loved the game then after some hrs of playing the game I noticed something very wired so I was flying with my starship from system to system then I decided to land on an random planet after playing on that planet for a while I wanted to Explore something else. I went back to my ship and Entered it and I Noticed a huge FrameDrop. I had like 5-10fps in the ship so I was like What the ♥♥♥♥? I launched the ship out from the planet the framedrop was there for like 1min and then it just stopped and went back to about 80-110fps. Next Day I spawn in the Space Station entered my starship and I get this huge fps drop again and this time it lasts for an endless time and never stops.  I land on a plant after taking 10min to get there with this low frame I went out from the starship and my fps was back to 80-110. I jump back in the starship and I have like 5-10fps? This game is awesome I recommended it to everyone and I think the developers will fix all these annoying frame drops and crashes for some players. The GamePlay 5/10 (Edit) -Played the game for abit more and i must tell u guys this game is ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ ♥♥♥♥ and its ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ ♥♥♥♥♥♥ i do not req this game to anyone sorry. This is not the game i payed for. Rate it now 2/10 becasue of the 5% this game has to offer. I asked for a refund and i hope i get it if not i will need to slap some happygames butts. (Edit) Forgot to Thumb down the game.", "appid": "275850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198012149198", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funn