{"text": "This game weighs like 8/9 MBs so it can be downloaded within a second, I think. Well, it costs 0,79€ so I guess it's ok, since it's the minimum Steam price for a game as far as I know. Let's not talk about the soundtrack - it's so horrible that I can't even put it into a genre. It's like a 1-minute loop taken from the '90s. The game features 25 levels and it's basically a platformer - non-remappable keys are WASD, or something else like space and the directional keys, plus you can wall jump. Bad thing is that the controls suck and are unresponsive, so your slime-character will float left and right and land where he wants. The game consists of a series of short levels in which you'll have to jump, avoid obstacles, collect coins (useful only for skins) and eventually reach the end. The graphics are quite basic and they follow the same scenario - there's the blue sky thing you can see in the Steam store page and little else on the background, while the obstacles and the platforms and such are made with some kind of square-shaped brown blocks. The wall jump is implemented in a crazy way and it will probably make you ragequit within some levels, but the main problems lie on the last levels - which are definitely too hard and frustrating. So all in all another indie platformer with nothing new to offer apart from some hours between boredom and frustration. Not a total negative review from me here but it's really nothing worth to play in my opinion.", "appid": "1138290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198356141989", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589025600.0}
