{"text": "I'm really getting tired of this unfinished re-released mess of a game that claims to be \"Definitive Edition\"  Update changes can be found the the end of review. Disclaimer: Just because i have received it for free since i own the classic copy, it dosn't mean that i should tolerate the progressively lower quality end product, ESPECIALLY since it was better before. So i will try to inform the new buyers to what they are signing in for. The graphical uplift is barely noticeable to classical version. Sure there are some changes like; super shinny surfaces, better makeup for our ageing characters, altered weapon sounds and God like car lights that can blind the blind person. Oh yeah and there is two new cars; One ported over from Mafia 3 (with terrible damage model) and Mafia's 1 taxi Falconer only available during winter time? And that is it. Can't think of anything else atm. The game is still missing 2 vehicles from \"Made Man Pack\" weird considering This Is \"Definitive Edition\" Now on to RNG Bugs: Every time you start the game you have a random chance to get rare, common or Legendary bug. ps. Epic bug just crushes your game to your desktop, at anytime of ur playtime... Sometimes unloaded textures, sometimes unloaded Text. Sometimes no sound or smt. no minimap. Ohh and don't get me started on tailing missions, because you have a really good chance to repeat the whole BORING and SLOW section, just because the opponent is a total derp at driving and gets stucke on other cars, thus game decides to call it a day (failing mission) since you can't go up to him and help him out.. obviously. Get use to it, this trend is becoming the new norm.  \"oh but i got it for free, ehh its oke\" Good attitude..  xD Mafia 1 Remake goes live in about 2 months xD \"its oke\" and yes i know  its not Hangar 15 who worked on this rrrresalle of mafia 2, they worked on Mafia 3 xD I will keep review updated if something changes in upcoming weeks or a month.  But im not willing to download 44GB again just because they woke up and decide to release patch months later. Warning! Spoilers Ahead!.. sort of, its to help you save time. Ps. This re-release should be called \"Definite Joke Edition\" of once glorious game The Mafia 2. Review note changes 01/06/20 Remove unnecessary spaces. I'd like to say that there is still a problem with earning some basic achievements which otherwise you would normally unlock easily. Review note changes 18/06/20 + Enforcer achievement can be now unlocked, and main campaign stats are now correct.  Fun fact. Direct @k support website isn't helpful at all. good luck reporting bugs. - Jimmy's Vendetta stats are still broken, preventing (me?) from obtaining other achievements like; Massacre, Sharpshooter, Firebug and Armament King. (Yes i did verify steam files). - Still no \"Made Man\" pack cars available. (yes Iam linked to 2K) - Weird fps drop that have not been present before. (Jimmy's vendetta) As of now. Final Review note 26/06/20 This game will be uninstalled after I have finally reached 100% complition.  Summery: + Nostalgia  - I fell like this rerelase didn't deliver much of an experience like classic version did and some of us had a problems running it at 60FPS (it was all over the place). Some didnt have the problems but had same bugs scattered throughout the game despite their glamourus PC machines. - Corrupted save games. (but i've managed to fix that, i will explain below) So for same reason, good or bad. This game had my old (classical) auto-saves already present when I first installed the game. Most of which where negative sums that are closer to  UK national Debt (of about -2.3 trillion)[-4.8Tril to be exact if counted all liabilities because of some F*#ki@! lockdown decision!! of a thing that might be just a flu! And Kill Bill is talking about 2nd wave!] alright ok ok... So i fixed that.. you know how? xD  I have copied and pasted my old save games from Classical superior version to DAssE save folder. AND...   I was able to finish the rest of the missing achievements and my game run lot smoother without bad FPS drops  EXAMPLE: Sigh Edition Save games files location  C:\\Users\\username\\Documents\\my games\\Mafia II Definitive Edition\\Saves\\76561198020397259   Classical Masterpice save location C:\\Users\\username\\AppData\\Local\\2K Games\\Mafia II\\Saves\\76561198020397259 (save you old ones just in case)  And.. bada boom bada bing peter pan stephen king! it worked. Thats it. Im out.  bye", "appid": "1030830", "steamid": "profiles/76561198020397259", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590580800.0}
