{"text": "I was very much looking forward to this game, and actually preordered it before completion. That was a mistake. First off, i remember seeing \"Co-op Campagin\" early on in one of the features the game would have. It did not have this at its release. This leads on to the previous installment Stronghold 2, which was, in my opinion, a catastrophe. I've never played a game with so many bugs, so much that the campaign was unplayable, and I mean really unplayable - The game would simply crash. Looking at the first installment in the series Stronghold. This first one was actually pretty good. There was still an amount of bugs or glitches, but it was playable, and I really liked that one. The memory of the good times I had with the first game, was probably what made me buy this one. I made a mistake... Firefly Studios really screwed me over on this. Stronghold 3 is just another messy, buggy and awful game. The game was clearly not complete when they released it, and it goes to show how good Firefly Studios is. This will be the last game I buy from them, without atleast trying the demo first.", "appid": "47400", "steamid": "profiles/76561197992566607", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1322308800.0}
