{"text": "I know someone has already addressed what I'm going to mainly talk about but I just wanted to give more in depth details about the whole situation. So basically I bought the game (YES I actually paid money for this game. I know this game was given out for free but I missed it) and played for like an hour or so (The rest of the time I spent idling for cards). From the hour or so I played I probably experienced over 100 glitches. Glitches include but not limited to - crashes, cliping through items, falling off the map, stamina not recharging, not being able to do any damage to enemies, enemies not being able to do any damage to you, not being able to pick up items, not being able to accept certain quests, terrible AI, freezing etc. I could keep going but the list is endless. So anyway I took a screenshot of the game and just simply criticized it for being what it is - A completely broken, rushed for Early Access, ♥♥♥♥♥♥ game. After about four days or so I get a response from the developer... \"do some research how can you get the impression that this is a finnished game when there is about 900 warning that say \"in dvelopment\" and \"early access\", yes 100% complete... great intelligence skills you have there....\" Screenshot of screenshot:  Screenshot of responses:  Seeing the developer insult someone over criticizing their game (which totally deserves it) is appalling. I encourage all of you to not support a developer who gets so butthurt like this. I paid actual MONEY for this game. I fully deserve to criticize it. The developer can just not take criticism and goes out of his way to actually insult someone over it. This is absolutely unacceptable. Please do not support developers who are like this. My screenshot has been taken down due to a violation of Terms of Service. As you can see from the screenshots above I have done nothing wrong whatsoever. I'm not sure what happened but I have contacted Steam Support about this issue. Hopefully it will be revoked. Maybe the developer reported/flagged the ♥♥♥♥ out of it? Who knows. The developer also seems to like to flag negative reviews and ban people who don't like his \"game.\" I wouldn't be surprised if the developer flagged this review in all honesty. So all in all, DO NOT BUY THIS GAME DO NOT GIVE THE DEVELOPER YOUR MONEY DO NOT PLAY THIS GAME DO NOT SUPPORT THIS GAME DO NOT SUPPORT DEVELOPERS WHO ARE LIKE THIS", "appid": "382240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065929855", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "126", "votes_funny": "24", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1455192000.0}
