{"text": "The game overall is great, however there are a lot of very questionable design choices that can ruin the experience. The devs seem to hate what made insurgency insurgency they tried to go in the complete opposite direction but overall its hurt the game. 1: All SMGs just plain suck or are too expensive to make decent, their stupid high H recoil means a comp is a must for most of them in sight lines longer than 20m. Meanwhile the far superior choices like the MK18, VHS, M4, G36, any of the AKs or the super cheap 2 point shotguns exist. 2: The idea of increasing the size of the restricted zone to prevent spawn camping failed. It doesn't work when you have sight lines far away that look practically into spawns and you can rocket or mow them down with an MG spawn. With the restricted zone being so huge any flanking is basically impossible and the only reasonable way to take an objective is to spam smoke and/or fire support and zerg rush in. It can lead to intense moments but its not interesting or rewarding.  3: Doing well is no longer based on how good you are at FPS games, how experienced you are with your gun or coordination with your team. It's now knowing the best spot to camp where no one knows where you are and can shoot people in the back. Before if you were against a good player you could recognise where they usually were, what they rushed, what corners they didn't check, if they liked to spawn camp, if they liked to flank or secure buildings with their team and could exploit that, it was \"tactical\", now trying to kill a good player is just hide and seek where you will get shot in the butt periodically. 4: it's just not that well optimised, you will still get stutters and fps drops on high end systems. It seems like the jank of insurgency was replaced by staler meat grinder gameplay which, for me, I cannot say is an improvement. It seems more like battlefield than insurgency now.", "appid": "581320", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135024119", "voted_up