{"text": "Well I had much more expectations than this to be honest since I played RE2 Remake last year and compared to original that one was a blast! it has amazing puzzle, great atmosphere and it was obvious that the dev team put their entire time on single player campaign and the story, but this one was just more like a reskined RE2 Remake for me, enemies was not challenging as RE 2, puzzle?! I don't think I even ran into any sort of thing that can be called puzzles!? while RE2 had tons of those with amazing design and twists. So I can say 70 to 80 percent of the game's areas are borrowed from RE2 Remake, So it's kinda boring going all those places with much much less challenges! MR.X in RE2 was really amazing but Nemesis in this was completely ignorable and you could kinda easily leave him behind and let him scream \"STARS\"!!! for how much he likes caz he's not gonna bother you and just gonna shout that voice once in a while :) also there are no multiple endings in this one I believe caz you won't get many choices in the game and the way is completely straight forward and all you have to do is to walk in the line :) So in my humble opinion paying full price for this game is not wise and I think if you can grab it on a sale for up to 70% it's kind of a good deal! I'm not even gonna bother to head to MP portion of the game, caz I already know that part has nothing special for me while great MP games like Dead by Daylight are out there! So CAPCOM if you intended to screw the RE 3 Remake, I can say with confidence, Well Done! you did it! you disappointed the fans! this game could be another masterpiece like RE 2 Remake, but CAPCOM seems did not intended so!", "appid": "952060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198066551850", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1586088000.0}
