{"text": "Blitzkrieg franchise... one of the finest real time wargames I ever played. So many sleepless nights and short days with the common feeling  - just one more mission... Years have passed, many new wargames were released and I did my best to try them all. Some were good, some not that good ... and the rest just plain awful. And here is where I would place Blitzkrieg 3. Shameful use of the old franchise name to make a game, that has hardly anything in common with its legendary predecesors. If you loved the first (still the best) and the second part (had potential). Then please DON'T spoil yourself your memories on those great games and avoid Blitzkrieg 3 as a plague. I did try to like this game, I really did. But to no avail. The core basic of the new game is flawed and no matter what they update this is still a dumbed down wanna-be wargame aimed at... God knows whom. So in short: - forget about nice missions from the originals. You will get some annoyingly scripted missions without a darn auto save. - forget the use of single soldiers (except snipers), here you get a whole squad as in Company of Heroes series - forget the usage of combined arms as in the original. Here you only need a ton of tanks/tanks destroyers and a sniper/scout vehicle. Infantry you say? Not really needed here where you are on offence and a really limited value on the defence only. - graphic are nothing special for today's standard. Animations are ok. Maybe too spectacular... but hey... kids like BIG BANGS. - Multiplayer is boring. Base building in Blitzkrieg franchise? No thanks... Rest in peace Blitzkrieg franchise and thank you for nice memories.", "appid": "235380", "steamid": "profiles/76561198008527916", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "68", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1473163200.0}
