{"text": "Набор чужих изображений, разбитых на скудное количество частей, которые не сопоставит разве что умственноотсталый ребёнок. Единственный пазл, который заслуживает внимания - Киану Ривз, да и то его решение происходит в основном методом тыка и перетаскивания основной массы кусочков по всему полю. Музыкальный фон не раздражает, но при \"решении\" вышеупомянутого изображения Киану со временем очень надоедает. Что касается достижений, то в наше-то время, когда за счёт ачивок разработчики зарабатывают деньги на дроч€рах, STREAMWORKS могли и постараться добавить с десяток более-менее красивых иконок за полученные \"успехи\" покупателей. Покупать исключительно для коллекции и по скидке да и то только после одобрения Steam'ом, если это и произойдёт вообще.", "appid": "1108400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198062493944", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "8", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565870400.0}
{"text": "I've given this a positive review before but with the last update, one of the few good things that this game had is now ruined. I'll start with the positives. The guns and loot in general are absolutely fantastic. This is what a shooter looter should strive for, legendaries that feel distinct, unique and fun to use. The guns have improved considerably in visuals, sound and feel from BL2 and so has the inventory menu and the bank space. Right now I have 400 bank space which is a very good thing. I am also not getting any menu lag in inventory screen like I regularly did in BL2. Gameplay is also improved from BL2. Obviously, the guns are better as mentioned above but the whole thing feels a lot more fluid. The level design is very good and every area now has a teleporter which makes the commute a lot less tedious than it was previously.  Visuals and audio in this game are quite good. Graphically, the game is an evolutionary improvement on BL2 and sound seems a little better too. The environments are varied and interesting. This is where the good things end with BL3, it's all downhill from here. The vehicles still have that stupid mechanic where the it always drives in the direction of the mouse pointer. That ♥♥♥♥ felt old and stupid in the first BL game and that was a decade ago. I won't dwell too much on the story but it is bad, very very bad. The writing is terrible, the characters are either entirely forgettable or annoying and the villains are the worst in the history of the franchise. It is so bad that I started skipping all cutscenes half way through the playthrough. I don't think I missed anything of value since I felt the dying screams of my perishing braincells when I was watching the cutscenes in the first half of the story. They are a potent mix of cringe and aggressive stupidity that are actively bad for your IQ unless it's already in double digit values. Performance wise the game is not in a good spot. The forums have had a lot of topics on stuttering and frame drops. I've had frequent stuttering and my system comfortably exceeds the recommended specs. Also, a lot of people are reporting a lot of issues with the coop side of things. Overall, this seems like a pretty lazy console port which is disappointing because Gearbox had 6 months to fix this before it was released on Steam. There are also a considerable amount of bugs such as flying enemies getting stuck in arenas. The worst sin this game commits is in its endgame which is bread and butter for aRPG games. Previously, the endgame ended with Mayhem 4. In this mode enemies had 10 times the amount of hitpoints compared to normal mode, there were some random modifiers also but more than anything the endgame amounted to fighting giant bulletsponges. Naturally, it was pretty poor and limited the amount of viable legendaries and build variety severely. Fastforward to recent patch and Mayhem has been \"reworked\" and by that I mean that there are 10 levels now and in the last level enemies have 125 times the hitpoints of the normal mode so we went from giant bulletsponges to ludicrous bulletsponges. Needless to say, this made the previous problem of low number of viable weapons much, much worse. Without any exaggeration, in a game with several hundred unique and legendary weapons less than 10 are viable in endgame. There is no more experimentation and there is no more general farming because you know that 99% of what you are about to pick up will not work at all in endgame. I wish I was exaggerating that number but unfortunately I am not, legedaries drop like rain but only about 1% are worth picking up. Now you just farm designated drops for that tiny number of items that will deal enough damage to move those enormous health bars more than 1 pixel at a time. To add to this game's endgame woes, it has a lot fewer farmable bosses than BL2 did and a lot fewer arenas and raid bosses. This game is buggy, has a ♥♥♥♥ story, performs poorly on a PC that is significantly more powerful than the recommended spec and has the worst endgame in the history of the franchise. The few things that this game does well are well outweighed by everything that it does badly.", "appid": "397540", "steamid": "profiles/76561198006217347", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1584619200.0}
