{"text": "This game's ambitious. Don't get me wrong, the idea of a zombie semi-open world survival game - one that's driven by real time clock is interesting. But there's a few things that's wrong with this game. The major issue with this game is there's no actual plot character in this game. Everyone and anyone here can be killed and once the initial characters are dead you're left with characters who for some reason share the same voice actors as the ones who were killed off. The real time clock for me is both a negative and positive. It's a very interesting and novel idea to scavenge for loot as it depletes daily. But once the novelty wears out all it does is force you to come back to the game way too often for my liking. Moreover building and upgrading stuffs can take hours real-time so it's really a chore. Also the PC port is really barebones. I'm talking PS2-era PC port barebones here. it lacks any advanced options in-game. All in all it's a really ambitious game marred with flawed execution.", "appid": "329430", "steamid": "profiles/76561198135186315", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599566400.0}
