{"text": "There could be a good game in here. The combat is fun if a little wonky with the counter prompts and a little too generous with the knockback, but it's enjoyable enough action. The character design is fun and the world is interesting, with a decent amount of enemy variety at least in the bit i've played. But I can't recommend this game to anyone. Absolutely nobody. Unless maybe that person is a game developer with a deep-seated loathing for player agency and non-linear games. So it's a game with a narrator, but there are options to ignore what the narrator says and go different directions to explore. Kind of like the Stanley Parable. Also like the Stanley Parable, the narrator gets confused about what you're doing and tries to make you follow his directions. Unlike the Stanley Parable, however, the narration in this game wears out its welcome almost immediately. Go off the path here and he rants for 10 minutes about achievements. Go off the path there and he makes you watch a five minute cutscene. Go off the path over here and he rants at you about how you must hate this game so much if you're ignoring him, then takes you to a locked room with a goldfish simulator, then a meat boy-ish platformer before berating you about how much you suck and how good it will feel to follow his directions next time. They make a point, have a funny joke about it, and then continue on for about 15 more minutes grinding that point and any humor there might have been into the dust. It is completely overbearing and I don't want to interact with it anymore. Well you might say, why not just follow his directions then? Because those alternate paths are in the game. They programmed them to be there. It is content they intended for you to see, because if they didn't then they wouldn't have created it. They are offering this choice and then punishing you for choosing. It's actively malicious against its player. Good effort guys, but maybe try again once you get the chip off of your shoulder.", "appid": "553640", "steamid": "profiles/76561197972662016", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1512820800.0}
