{"text": "First of all I'll give this a Not recommended. -Unless- Its got a good sale going on. I've never been a huge fan of diablo esk games, I don't hate them, I just need someone to play with. So my friend and I grabbed the game and its expansions. First of all if you're looking for fun skills... neither one of us found anything overly enjoyable... The entire game is pretty relaxed in difficulty, we played on Normal mode with the Veteran Tag. I know that if you'd go on higher difficulties it will be \"harder\" and thats fine, sadly they are locked at start. We would have played through it again on elite had it been enjoyable the first run. Skill wise, feels like the games mostly auto attack-like skills... Graphic wise.... Well its an old game, it does well for its time.  Story wise... Well to be honest, it might be okay, I got bored reading it rather early on and everytime I tried to get back into it, didn't really improve. Playing on normal+veteran we kinda just walked all over the enemies... Even the \"final\" bosses of the main campaigns kinda fell in like... 20? maybe 30 seconds... Myself just standing there letting skeletons beat on the bosses, while my buddy would just spin2win.  Now really I don't think the games -bad- I just think they lost out in certain areas. as my Buddy being a huge diablo nut, he kinda just said to me \"We should have just gone and played Diablo 2 or 3\"  Game has a lot of potential, just falls flat on skills. Class mixing is a good idea, the devotion board is probably the neater feature of the customization aspect. But overall the game was just not -fun- Wait for a sale if you're interested in grabbing it. Grab it with a friend or friends.", "appid": "219990", "steamid": "profiles/76561198023769441", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1588420800.0}
