{"text": "I have to admit that I am not a big fan of shooter games or war games in general for that matter. I find most of them to be repetitive and boring, no real point to them aside from gloating I suppose. I find that they draw a very toxic community that I rather not be a part of. I will say this game has a horrible community from what I have witnessed. It's somewhat similar to how people might have acted in Xbox Lobbies in Black Ops which I'm sure most of us have experienced. If that's your thing, cool, but I prefer not listening to children scream when I'm trying to play a game. The best thing to do in this situation, obviously, is to mute everyone. I just find it unfortunate that I have to resort to that but I'm aware that there isn't much the developers can do to prevent this.  The real issues I have with this game is how *boring* I find it. I find it absolutely stale and I hate it. You also cannot play a death match game because it's full of hackers and no one cares to even try and stop it. The hacking in this game is insane and everyone does it since there is no real security. There is no reason to even touch online unless you're playing ranked or with your friends because you cannot beat hackers. As soon as you spawn you're shot and killed, it's truly lame.  The only reason I ever load this game is when I've exhausted every other option and I feel like playing against bots. I quite literally have not touched an online game in a long time aside from seeing if hackers are still an issue. I just join and leave. This game is very dated and should have been upgraded long ago given it's success.  I do not suggest or recommend this game to anyone who is uninterested in fighting bots over and over. The game is a worthless investment of time.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561198867770532", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581595200.0}
