{"text": "Как игра стала бесплатной, читеров стало в 10 раз больше на запретной зоне (мм и напарники все норм, потому что там демки записываются), а у меня прайм статус. Мусорный vac не работает от слова совсем. К некоторым в профиль заходишь, так они с апреля 20г читерят, а сейчас ноябрь. Почти каждая игра-репорт. Ради них раз в неделю и захожу. ok.", "appid": "730", "steamid": "profiles/76561197998107312", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1605614400.0}
{"text": "So they said that this game would take a while to complete but no, it only took me around 3 hours. It then tells you to play again to see what happens if I do things differently, but you feel no real conviction to go and do this. The game is much too short, the money that you get asked for goes up too high too quick as the game is that short. I was able to keep way above the asked pay from Bruce everyday, but it still meant I didn't really have any money to have any fun.  Also the only real way to make money in the game is to do illegal jobs for Bruce so you have to force your world into negative karma. You can buy guns in the game but it will take a while to get that money and even then you probably won't afford the ammo, however that doesn't matter because you can punch pretty much everyone to death and when you reach the endgame, weapons don't matter. The ending was so lukewarm and anti-climactic, but in a way also didn't make much sense.  Another anti-climactic element is if you fail to keep your family happy, healthy, fed and the house tidy or if you fail to pay Bruce. It's just a game over screen. I don't want to spoil the ending but trust me, it isn't fun or gratifying. It's really unsatisfying, just it's over, please play again. No, I don't think I will.", "appid": "904360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198313077013", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1590667200.0}
{"text": "Terza DLC di PAYDAY2 della serie Silk Road, DLC più che penosa, si vede sempre di più che è una dlc senza impegno solo per raccogliere una manciata di soldi per supportare lo sviluppo di PAYDAY3, fatta senza impegno cortissima (durata nemmeno 30 minuti) e scarna di dettagli. Il prezzo è mooolto più alto di quello che vale in confronto a missioni più belle che sono uscite a minor prezzo o che sono già nel gioco base. Se siete veramente fan di PAYDAY2 e volete supportare lo sviluppo di PAYDAY3 compratela pure, ma se volete semplicemente una missione in più, non fatelo ci sono già moooolte missioni fatte meglio nel gioco base.", "appid": "1347750", "steamid": "profiles/76561198164206194", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593604800.0}
{"text": "To put this bluntly, I'm dissapointed witht he 400 Days DLC. The first season of the Walking Dead was such a runaway success that we all craved more. However this 'episode' can't escape the feeling that it's simply just an attempt to cash in on the success of Season 1. As of right now there is nothing linking 400 days to the people or events of Season 1 so anyone looking for insight on the outcome of Season 1's cast will be dissapointed. It's unclear if the choices made in this DLC will have any bearing on Season 2 but I guess we'll find out. So unless you consider yourself a die hard fan of the franchise I'd say this episode is skippable.", "appid": "207620", "steamid": "profiles/76561197970522234", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1375617600.0}
