{"text": "I wanted to love this game I really did, but this game is just so tedious let me explain. DIVINITY ORIGINAL SIN 2 is an “open world” role playing game that gives you the feeling of being able to go and do whatever you want the feeling of being free. But in reality, you’re not this game has a very set in stone deliberate way of progressing. You can’t run off and farm mobs to level up as they don’t respawn this is amazing for emersion but sucks in reality. This means you have to do quest (which is fine) to progress and get experience to level up. But this is where my mane and only gripe with this game is. As Divinity tries to portray its self as this big amazing open world where nothing is off limits and where the story is yours to make. When in reality every new zone is just a check list of quest that you have to do in order to level up. This game very much forces you to do an invisible check box of quest beforehand and it sucks. Going off this invisible path set by the developers often leads to your death.   This game isn’t hard no one is sitting there going “oh my god this game is too hard I can’t possibly advance” People are obviously advancing but its tedious and annoying, not because this game is so “old school” or “hardcore” but because this game fails to hold up to its own principles, This games mapping system is somewhat reminiscent of “old school” rpgs games as in, it doesn’t give you an arbitrary waypoint to follow or to guide you, all it does is give you a “journal” update and sometimes a very vague waypoint to go to. In many places and parts of this game you are supposed to magically know how the devs want you to approach a particular quest, area or even a fight. Not knowing this vital information usually leads to your death or a restart of the zone. Divinity willing holds back information from the player. There is a difference between not holding the player's hand and dumping them into a situation that cannot be managed unless you already have firsthand experience or information. The best way to describe Divinity Original Sin 2 is that it’s a Wikipedia game you’ll spend most of your time alt tabbed googling what to do.", "appid": "435150", "steamid": "profiles/76561198249203506", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600862400.0}
