{"text": "There will be some minor spoilers in this review. With that in mind please bother to read it through because I had the ability to recently play this without the red tinted glasses and this is not a good game. Let's start at the beginning. The first three chapters of this game are amazing, they're full of thrills, atmosphere, suspense, and horror. The mansion at the beginning of the game has a backstory and \"enemies\" far more interesting than the rest of the game even offers. When you enter Innsmouth you instantly know something is up, the people are unfriendly to say the least, everyone is tinged a slight gray and have trouble speaking, those who aren't seemed scared and won't talk to you and mysterious people hang out in allyways. For three chapters you enjoy a thrilling investigation but that all ends once you reach \"Attack of the Fishmen\". This chapter starts out with a chase that scares you as you lock doors and struggle to bolt them behind you leaping through windows and across rooftops until finally you end up in a stealth section. That brings me to the first issue, this game's stealth is broken. Crouching and Stealth are confusing because both basically accomplish the same tasks, sneaking while crouching is useless and slows you even more while going into stealth while standing does absolutly nothing and enemies still see you. Enemies will often see you no matter what so if you do decide to play be prepared to die a lot and hope you manage to slink by. The next 4 chapters are a rage inducing slog including a mix of absolute boredom and rage enducingly hard areas. You try and sneak by and fail over and over again until eventually you manage to somehow run past all enemies and reach the stage where they decide to give you guns. Once they give you guns any ounce of fear you had remaining is instantly gone. Not that the fishmen are particulalry scary in the first place. They're just normal human enemies but slow and fat. They talk normally, they fight normally, it's all so boring. The game will attempt to scare you from time to time by showing you a girl that died earlier or the view point of some eldritch horror looking at some dudes but you never see anything scary. Eventually you save the guy you came to save and he makes you save his girlfriend who you met earlier. She is also vary obviously tainted by whatever disease plauges the town, this is not a spoiler because you can litterally see it on her face. After you save her you drive about five feet and both of the people you fought to save instantly die. At this point I was almost ready to give up after murdering tons of enemies in cold blood (the combat isn't hard in some scenarios and relies on cheap tactics like having some guy come around the corner with a machine gun to inflict damage on you) it was all for not and you somehow end up back in the nuthouse. Not even a day later you are sent back for Chapter 7 because the FBI says so. You continue to fight the same enemies as always except they took away all your guns except for your pistol. This area is a bland boring maze with endlessly respawning enemies that outgun you around every corner. I ended up having to stop playing at this point because this game honestly offers no enjoyment. Do not buy this game. After the first 3 (more like 2.3) chapters it has no horror value, no survival horror aspects, no interesting story, no interesting characters, etc. I could go on for ever about how the player character is boring idiot or about just how boring fighting human enemies in a game about Lovecraftian Horror can be but I won't continue to nag your ear. Look further to games like Silent Hill or Resident Evil. If you want Lovecraftian horror look anywhere else than this game. Edit: I decided to finally finish this game and let me tell you it was not worth it. I love a challenge and decided that seeing the end would be worth it and let me tell you it's garbage. Boring bad boss fights, a hastily wrapped up story, a reliance on stealth mechanics. All of this was present in the finale of Dark Corners. You end up killing the main antagonist with a single knife stab and killing the two supposed \"gods\" is a matter of doging slow attacks and doing basic actions to kill it. Avoid", "appid": "22340", "steamid": "profiles/76561198065238570", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1514376000.0}
