{"text": "The first chapter of this game is an abominable piece of garbage. First off, let me state that I love this franchise, and the opening to this one had me hooked. It does get some things right. The music, the atmosphere, and the initial gameplay is fantastic! I was loving the high that was the first sequence, but upon entering the first trial, my opinion of the game crashed and burned harder than the Hindenburg.  This game actively insults your intelligence. It portrays somewhat-dynamic possibillites and scenarios to flesh out an investigation, and then pulls a 180, after more than two hours of development. Speaking of which, why does the first trial last nearly three hours? And let me just tell you, they fit A LOT of puzzles in that time, most of which is boring and uninspired, and by the 12th time you're doing a puzzle, you just want to get it over with. Learning all of the instructions for the puzzles themselves isn't hard, but it's too tedious, and that subtracts even further from the enjoyment.  SPOILERS AHEAD But back to what I was saying, the first trial ends up being a complete insult to your intelligence, as the culprit turns out to be YOU. It doesn't show any clues that might've led you to think this, and the execution of it in general is not fitting for this type of game, let alone this franchise. All of the actual \"clues\" to this preliminary 3 hour long event are purposefully kept from you, and done off screen. It's lame, through and through.  I've heard that the game picks up greatly (and then eventually crashes and burns once more) after chapter 1, but there is no excuse for the piece of garbage \"Prologue\". I don't give excuses to movies that are terrible for 3/4ths of the run time, and make the final quarter memorable, so I'm not giving this a pass either.  Thanks for destroying my expectations. I can't wait to see how bad the rest of this is.", "appid": "567640", "steamid": "profiles/76561198174633726", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "2", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589198400.0}
{"text": "Не знаю почему \"люди\" так фанатеют по этой \"игре\", но ничего нового я вообще не увидел. Да, есть уровни где надо пару раз ошибиться, чтобы пройти до конца, но в этом нет ничего особенного. Право якобы выбора, предоставленное игроку в конце уровня в виде диалога - пустышка, потому что есть только единственно верный ответ, по сути тут лживый выбор без отсутствия альтернатив. Оформление и стилистика - обычные.  Под итогом могу сказать, что это очередной браузерный мусор, направленный на аниме дебилов/дрочеров, которые сами б раскрутили игру по сарафанному радио, с чем они и справились. Спасибо, что хоть за бесплатно, за такое платить вообще грешно.", "appid": "1289310", "steamid": "profiles/76561198093747292", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "11", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603886400.0}
