{"text": "It's not DN3D for sure. But is it good FPS? Is there any challenge? Not really. Game is ridiculously easy on hard. There is also \"Expert\" dificoulty - but you have to finish game first to unlock it. And it's not much harder. You don't have to search for key-cards - now you mash space like idiot now and then.. Seriously - wtf? Sounds made by weapons are weak - even devastator feels like toy. Boring fights. A lot of arenas where enemies spawn - but they are nice enough to not force you to fight with more than 3 of them at once. Overpowered weapons is something I loved in dn3d but they were rare and there was not thet much ammo for them (except secrets maybe). Here - we have a lot of crates that gives you infinitive ammount of ammo of any type. So basically combo schrink-ray + machinegun will let you end hardest enemies in seconds. Also 2 weapon slots kills fun. You can change that in options to 4 gun slots - but that allows you carry schrink ray (or expander in dlc) for almost whole game and that makes it even easier. I had some fun with this game. It was playable and had some nice moments. Can't recommend it though. Maybe with big discount. But only for people without huge expectations.", "appid": "57900", "steamid": "profiles/76561198082881386", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602849600.0}
