{"text": "I was kind of expecting to be - not too polished indie game, but, oh, boy ... there are some very big \"flaws\" in this game. Firstly, the game looks \"impressive\"and that's the best part of the game. Everything else is worse, much worse! Animations of characters are not good and in cut-scenes mostly without any emotional expressions, which really spoils the immersion into the game. The sounds seemed okey, but the music is much better. You move through the whole game on a very linear path, pressing the same button (when the icon pops-up) for climbing up, climbing down, walking between the walls, on the ledges - all with the same ol' button. You can't go back, once you did that (and that's really bad:). I was hoping for combat (which is the core of that type of game) to be as good and fluid as, maybe, in Darksiders or, at least, in Prototype 2, but, man, the combat is awful - really clunky, stuttering, frame-dropping and not enjoyable at all! I was expecting an average story, but with that \"theme setting\" it could be so much much more. Like the cut-scenes are made and dialogs so poorly written, it reminds me on games dated back all to year 2008. Innovations? The game's setting is nice, the graphical atmosphere is great, some of your unique skills are good, the idea behind the main character and in what he evolved ... but, no, that's just not enough. Not for the price that the game is listed for and not for the type of the game that Devil's Hunt wants to be. Sorry, just not enough.", "appid": "887720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071243651", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1569067200.0}
