{"text": "Really not that good of a puzzle game.  First of all, they're circles - not spheres. Puzzles are mostly a matter of timing.  You place circles on a track and they move around the track and must not collide with other circles doing the same thing.  The trouble is, on many levels the tracks are of different lengths, and the lengths are not multiples or fractions of each other so unless you are quick to complete the level, two circles on different tracks will eventually go out of phase enough that they will inevitably collide. So there is a bit of planning to a difficult level but it isn't all that satisfying.  Hey, it's still better than SNIK though!", "appid": "399530", "steamid": "profiles/76561198013520503", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1510833600.0}
