{"text": "It tries hard but never succeeds. It throws at you some lovecraftian stuff but makes it in a comedy way. And even in this it fails miserably. The whole humour seems to be more teenagers-orientated and not really funny. You can't just take some lovecraftian terms, mix them with lazy students chit-chat and be done with it, it just doesn't make it together.   It tries to be more than a kinetic VN: it introduces a new mechanic: click-to-interact, but even this aspect is totally linear. You just click on every piece from left to right and be done with it. One more fail. The story starts very slowly. It shows you tons of characters but most of them seem to exist for the single purpose of being \"funny\". The story ends quite abruptly and doesn't reveal any motivation behind the characters. It just throws facts at you. The protagonist is stupid as hell, but at least it is said in the plain text. Technically it also has some flaws. The most part of text is written in caps which is more difficult to read, Steam overlay doesn't work (you can't make screenshots the usual way). The menus are also quite poor-made, there is no settings, no coming back and almost no sounds. At least the art is made well.  I know this game was on Kickstarter and they promised it to be completely different: a platformer shooter or something. Seems like there were some big problems with development team. Maybe that's why the game is cut off and not polished.", "appid": "870290", "steamid": "profiles/76561198071848932", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1589544000.0}
