{"text": "I remember when Yu-Gi-Oh first came out. So, it was fun reliving a bit of my childhood, but I realized as a card game, it has gone downhill. Now most duels against people, when they have the cards they want, last about five turns, if you are lucky.  Gone are the days of trying to get 2 or 3 monsters out, so that you can summon you ace. And, most of the time, you win or lose before you even get that ace out because your deck was better or worst than the other guy's. Now I see more and more decks that after their first turn they have two 3000 attack monster out. Sure, it has always been about getting a stronger monster out than the other guy, but back then, you played with most of your deck to get that stronger monster out. I just miss the days of drawing a card in a really cool way and watching and feeling the emotions with each card played.", "appid": "601510", "steamid": "profiles/76561198142172891", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "12", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1554638400.0}
