{"text": "They started this game   and  , many  ,   and adding  , but after couple years, they   it and moved on to their  .  you still reading this? why?? is the reason above not enough for you to not buy this game and avoid it at all costs? ok ok. ill tell you my reasons why you should avoid this game.  -tutorial is terrible -loading screens are way to long  -game saves are very rare and in order to not lose hours of progress, you gotta remember to click that save button(where are we, in early 2000 when a save button was a thing?) -no alert/warning of any sort when a thief steals something from your shop -no option to close your shop or end the day whenever you want in order to re arrange your shop, or just quit the game and manage your real life stuff. -your home doesnt have any use, except displaying some random trophies that the game didnt even notify you that you got them and when you got them... -when a vegetable is fully grown, many times when you try pick it up, it just vanishes and you never receive your crops -you can only accept 1 quest at any given time and only way to check the accepted quest progress is to go all the way back to your shop and check the quest board -items in quest book are very small icons and there for really hard to figure out what items are requested from you to finish the quest, unless you go back to your shop and check the quest board ONCE AGAIN... -shop organization list is very bad and needs allot of improvement and options to sort items by helmets, armors, swords and so on... -no way to see what gear is better for your champion and if its worth putting it on him or not in order to make him stronger -in skills firstly unlock the \"customer talk I\", it will help you at beginning, lvl 2 and 3 you dont really need, even later in game -avoid unlocking different customer classes(mage, rogue and druid) until you first unlock everything else, reason behind it is, if you unlock for example a mage, he will only accept potions, mage armor. but quests ask from you mostly to sell armor, weapons  and potions, so youll have very hard time finding \"armor\" npcs to sell them the armor, swords, shields. -farming is broken most of the time so no point in unlocking it all, but if you do decide to unlock it, youll get quests to sell 30 weed or some other vegetable, and like i mentioned above, you cant gather fully grown crops most of the time Even in this unfinished and abandoned stage of the game, its still fun for couple of hours, but i highly recommend everyone to buy this game only when its on sale, otherwise not really worth it. but yet again, its only 4 euros full price, so you decide, but i suppose you get what you pay for.", "appid": "381120", "steamid": "profiles/76561198056784623", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "9", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1575374400.0}
