{"text": "While being an improvement over the GRID2 flop, it still fails to deliver. Physics were a hot topic, GRID2 was all about drifting, Autosport returns to a more traditional formula, but cars still feel very wonky. Unfortunately the car setup options are extremely limited and I sometimes got caught by surprise as my car lost control or straight up understeered into walls. AI is extremely aggressive and they'll knock the player around without hesitation. They also seem to be impervious to things such as damage and tyre wear, making endurance races a chore. Also, don't ever expect your teammates to be useful. The game engine is still the same used in GRID2, which doesn't look bad. Unfortunately the car sounds aren't the greatest and the so called cockpit view is way too blurry to be used properly, just to mask the fact that nothing in the car is animated, something ridicolous for a 2014 racing game.", "appid": "255220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198013600314", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1497787200.0}
