{"text": "General things: To start off this game is not just the price you looking in the store, to be able to farm without getting suicidal feelings you will need to spend 40~ more euro to buy pets so they will loot for you; yes you can farm manually, but you will be killing millions of monsters. Will crouch to loot every single one? - Quick answer = NO. Yes you can buy this pets from the market but hey! Good luck! Another thing that you get a bit forced to buy (not as much as pets) is a ghillie costume, this one hides your name when you playing against other people, it won't ensure you a victory though those players you fighting will have to focus you like the double to be able to see you. Against some classes in the night you fight looking the map not the enviroment which is sad..  This costume is not sellable throught market so is completely pay to win (even if it would be sellable throught market it would be kinda of p2w since get pearl items from the market is very hard).There is an item called \"flare\" which allows you to see their name but hey it only lasts for 5 seconds or so, so this won't counter pay to winers. PvE: The thing which we call PvE in this game is not as other MMORPGs, you are not doing raids/dungeons with your guild every friday neither find parties to do them. You just got spots with mobs, TONS OF MOBS. You wanna be farming them to level up your character, get money or simply get a item drop from them. Another PvE concept in here is lifeskilling, the lifeskilling in here is way more extended than other mmo's. You can almost play like a lifeskiller in here without doing any other PvE content and you sure won't get bored of it if you enjoy the lifeskilling thing (get money from it, upgrade your lifeskill rankings, etc..). PvP (this is not the main concept of the game in my opinion because is greatly unbalanced): Let's be honest, to feel yourself able to kill your adversary in a PvP arena/battleground you will need around 2.500 hours in this game to be able to get the gear to do it, so just simply forget about arenas/battlegrounds. As a guild member you can be part of a higher tier PvP (Conquest wars, Node wars) those you do with your guild, but as arenas/battlegrounds, you won't do anything if you are not correctly geared (here you can miss some gear since you got a team, you will need to play 1500 hours or so to get the gear to be able to do something more than just see) The PvP content you are going to do a lot likely or unlikely is PK (Player Kill), in this game you can turn on/off PvP (with ALT+C) which allows you to kill other players or allows other players to kill you. There's a main stat in here called \"Karma\" which allows low players to don't get camped by higher geared players. If that karma drops below 0 the guy is going to \"Negative Karma\", this guys can only go to their city Muiquun (which is located at the desert). If those die while in negative they can get their gear downgraded, crystals blown, exp reduce. To raise the karma you need to farm. There's a big bad thing here which are guild wars, If a guild is able to war your guild (it must be both prepared or both non prepared) these players can kill you anytime they want without any consecuence which is kinda sad if you are low geared and you are getting camped by a high gear guy.. You can of course leave your guild (you won't be able to join it or another back in 1 day) to make karma system do its job which I recommend if you suffer this from other players.", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198032681562", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511352000.0}
