{"text": "Back then i really enjoyed playing this game when i first got my laptop and created my steam account, the aesthetics were perfect, the characters were very original, the lores were interesting etc. and i grinded 900 hours into this game to have fun and be better cuz im very broke and with my situation in my personal life i cant get out of the house so thats why ive bin playing this daily. but as time went by, everytime I'd feel frustrated because most of the players in all the game modes ecxept for custom are just super toxic. EVERYONE is toxic and the games performance has issues like the dodge and dashes not working and its not my laptop cuz ive played on another one which was a gaming laptop and a better pc than mine yet those actions still didnt work and the opponent would still hit me. This company focuses so much on adding new things every week for money without addressing the toxicity of the community as well as the issues in the game. Ever since i stopped playing i started getting better in multiplayers when it comes to my rage. Once i stopped playing brawlhalla its like i cut out something that was blocking me from being having fun and being happy when i play games. This game is not good for mental health. The community is VERY toxic, the games controls has issues and glitches and most importantly the devs are very greedy for money. This game can be good if they just put a little effort in getting it to where it needs to be. Dont pick up this game or waste your money on it. I REGRET spending over $30 on this game when i couldve spent my money on other things like all these halloween sales that i sadly cant get unless i beg and begging makes me feel like **** cuz i care about the other person and they wont give you back refunds cuz once you buy their packs your money is gone. Please theres better multiplayers out there than this game. I wish i could get back all my money and delete my hours.", "appid": "291550", "steamid": "profiles/765611989982573