{"text": "I played this game & at the end of the day feel like I was scammed. - Was not scary whatsoever. I don't see how introducing the classic learning technique of Flashcards is going to scare anybody. - You can genuinely see better in the dark than with any match or lantern. - The entire main group of characters are so rushed to the point the dead Explorer you come across is MORE INTERESTING than ANY other character in the game. ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥, can you imagine being so bored of the whole cast you want to play as the dead guy instead? - You literally cannot die & uninteresting enemies -- they man-handle you for 5 seconds til you have an anxiety attack, ♥♥♥♥ off, repeat. That's it. Absolutely no danger in the game. - Failing the same spot twice leads to just being placed AHEAD of it at the next checkpoint. Why bother trying when you can take a shortcut, eh? - Listening to a French woman constantly say \"little one\" & talk to herself throughout the entire game.  - ABSOLUTE BRAIN-DEAD IDEA to have a \"fear\" system where you can't simply take the SLIMMEST GLANCE at an enemy without having a damn stroke or anxiety attack - it's even more so ridiculous when you step into a dimly lit room for half a second & immediately start having a stroke because of it. Yeah, a dimly lit room or shadow gives me a heart attack, yet the next room I enter can be borderline pitch black & I'm just fine.  The story was as equally disappointing. How do you expect me to be gripped into a story when I feel like I'm playing some single mother's struggle to live with her child fighting with some welfare spirit that holds the papers to her approval? It seemed like the entire focus was on HER the whole way through. So much so that I suffered through a damn child-birth & breast feed scene.. If anything, I was hoping the \"doctor\" would chuck the ♥♥♥♥♥♥ out the nearest window like a football FOR me. There wasn't much \"lore\" to really find or get yourself \"immersed\" in either considering it all felt like a hot mess somebody with a newly added Liberal Arts degree under their belt wrote -- given the unnaturally specific setting & character you're playing as.  As for why I feel scammed? I paid $16 for a HL2 mod & found easily twice the enjoyment & content in that than this. TL;DR I literally just played through a mother's fight for her right to file for welfare. That's honestly how it felt to me. May as well make the ghost of your husband pay you for child support for \"leaving you\". TheLastOfUs2/10 - go play something else. Go play Outlast or Evil Within, maybe even Dead Space - this is just a live-action motion picture at best.", "appid": "999220", "steamid": "profiles/76561198080619474", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "16", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1603540800.0}
