{"text": "Why the ♥♥♥ are there NO penaltys for leaving the game before you die? Thats so big AF annoying when 3 out of 10 people leaves the room when it starts cause there arent impostor and 1-2 more for the next 2-3 minutes cause of democracy/serverlags/whatever Just give the game for more playstyle a \"Trust Score\", the higher the trust, so more trust from the other guys in you AND the game is VERY more difficult at the votes.  Players with negative scores or so cant leave lobbys until the round ends, afk players (afk for 1 minute) have the same big penalty like the players there just leave because \"i am not impostor mimimi\", and afk and \"i leave the game in the round because Just for fun\" players cant join a lobby for 5 minutes.... PLS Players that are alive can at the end from the round give some bonus score for 1 player like 10 points, other players from the winning faction there are dead can give 1 point But its a good game, dislike for your like :)", "appid": "945360", "steamid": "profiles/76561198095693076", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1601208000.0}
{"text": "I do not recommend this game because the combat system and boss fights are abysmal and are prime examples of poor game design. First off, all enemies outside of random encounter city brawls now regenerate health. Second off, most boss fights not only the boss himself, but also for the majority of the time the sidekick who can be extremely annoying. Third offm fights with lots of enemies are now packed inside tight quarters, so you have to fight 10+ enemies in a tight room (Stardust club fight, Tetsu dealer fight,) combine that with enemies locking onto you and performing their special move across the room (and also them regenerating health) makes for a very frustrating experience, oftentimes you'd be in a room with inner walls and you can end up with 10+ dudes gangbanging on you when you can't even see which direction you can dodge or run. Horrible game design. There are also very annoying details about the game world like the overabundance of side quests with long-winded intro dialogs that you stumble upon right when you're in the middle of going to point A, so you have to click multiple times to skip them. One very annoying detail is that you now don't get the chapter completion bonuses, so you have to be careful with your money now. Thus far playing the game has been a terrible and a very frustrating experience.  The new ability tree is horrible, since now you actually have to grind like it's some kind of an MMO to get enough XP or defeat Majima X number of times to get the upgrade. It's just plaint stupid.  In terms of pretty much everything, Y0 is a much better game. I'd rather fight Kuze 100 more times in Y0 than fight another Kiwami boss.", "appid": "834530", "steamid": "profiles/76561198018211867", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573473600.0}
{"text": "Just put you're finger in the door and smash it closed. Gets you the same feeling as playing this game. If you just wan't to buy it for the achievments (like me): don't.  You have to click at least an hour to get all of them. And if you do them in the wrong order (wich the game doesn't tell you), you can't even get some of them. And as the data is stored in the cloud, if you f*cked up the order, you can NEVER get the achievment. This is a worse version of Cockie clicker with a good title. Don't waste you're time and money for this \"thing\", because you really can't call it a game. 2/10 - Gives you some achievments but wastes you're time and destroy's you're finger.", "appid": "485890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198144739700", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1467374400.0}
