{"text": "A true spiritual successor to the good old mod from warcraft 3  with proper mechanics and gameplay, Unfortunately impaired by the horrible community and lack of Ranked optimisation options, the amount of MMR you receive or lose varies instead of being a solid number(so enjoyable when you lose 27 and gain only 19 the next match).  Insufficient monitoring on games and penalties to be applied afterwards to UNDESIRABLE players, progression is locked based on mmr and the ability to climb from solo que is nonexistent. I want to love this next proper step for the life cycle of dota so much but the negatives just keep piling up. Without a proper 5 stack team the games is utterly unenjoyable. In conclusion steps need to be taken to PURIFY the player base  FORCE proper behavior and reinvigorate solo queue experience. The lack of refund options for compendiums you've wasted time on  is also a Big no-no! After Many Patches and many positive changes (not enough to clean up the overall problems sadly) I can say with a clear mind that progress is slow somewhat in the right direction. As such I still cannot recommend you waste your time let alone spend money in this beautiful mess. The core team of devs supervised  by the Prophet frog, sadly focuses only on improvements from a perspective of the top tier international going few, creating a bit of roadblock with no new increase in talent from the rest of the player base, forcing them to be stuck in a hellhole-like situation filled with incompetent, angry, non-compliant russian children And as we all know if you cannot count on your team then why waste your time in the first place. The most prevalent and sorely needed features are still missing to date: - Personal ignore/banlist - do not match with blocked players from the list(concers and comment are known are irrelevant the filtration from this feature is minimal at best, even if you end up in a scenario of being machted with tiers far above you it can only yield in positive results i.e. force team work to occur, adapted with newer players , pass on knowledge with being an idiot ofc. ) - Sectioned regional locking, (many)separate (smaller)server categories based on region with Master regions only accessible via profile statistics i.e report rates, behavioural score etc. - MMR system redesign - although changes have been made they are sorely lacking. Mixing different tiers restriction should be outright removed, top tier player to mingle with the rest, to force a rapid change in behaviour and adaptability. - increase record count available", "appid": "570", "steamid": "profiles/76561198051496029", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "5", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1504699200.0}
